v1.2.3 round-26 (2026.7.19) — PGN Termination/comment配套修复 for FIDE 6.9 timeout draw:
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — fix round).
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _buildTerminationTag now correctly distinguishes
    timeout-win from timeout-draw. When _timeoutWinnerColor is null (FIDE 6.9
    insufficient-material draw), the Termination tag is
    `[Termination "Both flag fall / insufficient material"]` instead of
    `[Termination "Time forfeit"]`. Also added Termination tags for all other
    terminal statuses that were previously missing them: draw_insufficient
    → "Dead position", draw_stalemate → "Stalemate", draw_50move → "50-move
    rule", draw_75move → "75-move rule", draw_repetition → "Threefold
    repetition", draw_5fold → "Fivefold repetition", checkmate → "Normal"
    (PGN spec recommended value).
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _buildPGNString timeout comment now handles the
    draw case. When _timeoutWinnerColor is null, the last move's {} comment
    gets the new pgn_timeout_draw_insufficient i18n string ("超时但子力不足，
    和棋" / "Timeout but insufficient material, draw") instead of no comment.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _deriveGameResult now has explicit draw_* status
    branches that return '1/2-1/2' directly, instead of relying on the
    gameOver-text-includes-T('white_wins') fallback. Behavior unchanged but
    logic is clearer and no longer depends on localized text matching.
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3): new i18n key `pgn_timeout_draw_insufficient`
    (zh='超时但子力不足，和棋', en='Timeout but insufficient material, draw').
  - All other modules: No changes this round.
  - License classification: unchanged.

v1.2.3 round-25 (2026.7.19) — SonarCloud S6582/S3358 style cleanup + FIDE 6.9 timeout draw:
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — style + feature round).
  - All 11 JS modules (GPL v3 / AGPL v3 per existing classification): S6582 optional-
    chaining cleanup. A Python script (scripts/apply_optional_chaining.py) converted
    174 lines of `x && x.prop` → `x?.prop` across 8 files (ai-bridge.js 50, ui.js 33,
    game-logic.js 28, worker-pool.js 24, state-store.js 15, ui-interactions.js 10,
    chess960.js 8, eco-data.js 6). Only same-identifier && chains converted (semantically
    identical); typeof guards (round-11 design) and method-call chains (?.() changes
    `this` binding) skipped.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): S3358 nested-ternary flatten — 3 mate-label nested ternaries in
    _buildEvalTrendPoints and formatEval converted to if/else chains (semantically
    identical, more readable).
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): S3358 nested-ternary flatten — _findCriticalMoves NAG eval
    `cur.mate?(cur.mate>0?90000:-90000):cur.eval` → `cur.mate!=null?(...)`. Also fixes
    a latent falsy-0 bug: mate=0 previously fell through to the eval branch; now
    explicitly checked with !=null.
  - ui-gameflow.js (GPL v3): FIDE 6.9 timeout insufficient-material draw. _onGameClockExpired
    now calls isDeadPosition(gameState) before declaring the winner. If the position is
    a dead position (K vs K, K+minor vs K, K+B vs K+B same-color, K+B+B same-color vs K),
    the game is drawn by insufficient material instead of won on time. Uses the existing
    `draw_insufficient` status key and i18n string (`insufficient_draw`: zh='子力不足和棋！',
    en='Insufficient material!').
  - All other modules: No changes this round.
  - License classification: unchanged.

v1.2.3 round-24 (2026.7.19) — God Function split (S3776) + StatsActivity license fix:
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — refactor round).
  - ui.js (GPL v3): _renderReviewMode refactored from 552 → 357 lines (-35%).
    Extracted 8 helper functions + 1 module-level const:
    - `_RV_VA_COLORS` (module-level const): visual-annotation color palette,
      moved from inside _renderReviewMode so multiple helpers can share it.
    - `_computeRvBoardMetrics()`: pure function, computes review board sizing
      (cell size, label dimensions, full board height).
    - `_renderRvBoardCells(rBoard, flip, _rvCell, _rvCm, _rvCslMap, ...)`: renders
      the 8×8 board cells with control-map coloring, [%csl] highlights,
      coordinate labels, piece symbols, 🔁/⚡ markers.
    - `_renderRvArrowSvg(_rvCalList, flip, _rvCell, ...)`: renders the SVG arrow
      overlay for [%cal] visual annotations (dedup + per-color diagonal offset).
    - `_buildRvEvalBarHTML(_re, _rDelta, _rDepthStr, _rProgressStr, _rWdlStr)`:
      builds the eval bar HTML string.
    - `_buildRvSliderHTML()`: builds the review step-slider HTML.
    - `_buildRvChartHTML(_trendH, _trendW, _trendSVG)`: builds the eval-trend
      chart HTML wrapper.
    - `_buildRvNavHTML()`: builds the nav buttons (⏮ ◀ ▶ ⏭).
    - `_buildRvAnalyzeBtnHTML()`: builds the analyze-all button HTML.
    All helpers are function declarations (bundle-hoisted), take explicit
    parameters for local dependencies, and produce no side effects beyond
    reading module-level globals. No behavior change — every rendering path
    produces identical output.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): _reviewAnalyzeAdvance refactored from 218 → 171 lines (-22%).
    Extracted 2 helper functions:
    - `_findNextUncachedBatchStep(fromStep, lastStep)`: scans for the next
      uncached step (forward fast-path + full-range fallback for priority
      interruption). Consolidates the if/else nesting from the original.
    - `_triggerPendingPostBatchActions(_pendingSave, _pendingStats)`: triggers
      the pending PGN cache save + stats page open after batch completion.
      Eliminates S1192 code duplication (the completion branch had two copies
      of this ~15-line block — one for targetStep-valid, one for invalid).
  - ui.js (GPL v3): _resetGameUIState (231 lines) UNCHANGED. Analysis: the
    function is a flat sequence of `if(typeof X!=='undefined')X=null;` guards
    with no nesting. S3776 measures branching/nesting complexity, not line
    count — this function's cognitive complexity is already low. Forcing a
    split would add function-call overhead and require passing many module-
    level global references, increasing cognitive load. Documented as
    intentional design.
  - All other modules: No changes this round.
  - License classification: unchanged.

v1.2.3 round-23 (2026.7.19) — PR #51 CodeRabbit review fixes + SonarCloud triage:
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — fix round).
  - ui.js (GPL v3): Q4 — time-control dialog base/incr/delay `oninput`
    handlers now clamp out-of-range values (v>600/v>60) and write the
    clamped value back to the input box, eliminating the display-vs-state
    mismatch. Q5 — `_replayMovesToState` no longer silently skips null
    moveRecords at indices >0; only the intentional Black-to-move null
    placeholder at index 0 is skipped, any other null logs `console.error`
    and aborts the replay (returns null) to prevent annotation-index drift.
    Q6 — SPID input now rejects out-of-range values (<0 or >959) by
    clearing the input and setting `dlgChess960SPID=-1`, forcing re-entry
    (was: silently retained previous valid value, "see ≠ start").
  - ui-interactions.js (GPL v3): Q1 — non-Chess960 setup branch now clears
    `gameSPID=null` alongside `setChess960Mode(false)` so a stale SP-ID
    from the previous game cannot pollute PGN export / Shredder-FEN
    generation. Q3 — `stateHistory.push` and `_redoStack.push` now include
    a `clocks` snapshot via new `_snapshotClocks()` helper; `undoMove` and
    `redoMove` call new `_restoreClocks(snap)` to restore clock state,
    rebasing `lastMoveTimestamp` to `Date.now()` and restarting the tick
    interval if the saved state was running.
  - ui-gameflow.js (GPL v3): Q2 — `recordMoveEnd` now detects flag fall
    BEFORE applying the Fischer increment; if `remainingSec<=0` after
    deduction, it fires `_onGameClockExpired` and returns early without
    adding the increment, so 0+increment>0 can no longer mask a genuine
    timeout.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): Q10 — `_formatEvalDelta` no longer hardcodes
    the `+` sign; `dp=(Math.abs(d)/100).toFixed(1)` and the positive
    branch emits `+dp` while the negative branch emits `\u2212dp`
    (Unicode minus), consistent with the round-22 player-POV colour
    contract (a Black player improving no longer sees "+-1.2" in green).
  - tablebase.js (AGPL v3): Q1 — `importPGN` Chess960 branch now resets
    `gameSPID=null` BEFORE the FEN-derivation runs, so a failed
    `backRankToSPID` cannot retain the previous game's SP-ID. Q7 — tag-
    strip regex rewritten quote-aware: `/\[\s*\w+\s+(?:"[^"]*"|[^\]]*?)\s*\]/g`
    (was `/\[\w+\s+\S[^\]]*\]/g`), so values containing `]` (e.g.
    `[Event "Tournament [A]"]`) are no longer truncated. No ReDoS risk
    (mutually exclusive branches, non-greedy fallback).
  - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): Q8 — re-verified that `headerRe` is already
    quote-aware (`"((?:[^"\\]|\\.)*)" ` handles escaped quotes); no change.
    Recorded as a partial false positive.
  - All other modules (index.html.tpl, game-logic.js, chess960.js,
    pgn-standard.js, state-store.js, eco-data.js): No changes this round.
  - License classification: unchanged.

v1.2.3 round-22 (2026.7.18) — eval bar perspective fix (player-POV report):
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — fix round).
  - ui.js (GPL v3): formatEval() timeout & resign game-over branches now use
    `score:whiteWins?'+∞':'-∞'` (was `playerWins`) so the score stays
    White-POV and agrees with the player-POV emoji/desc — fixes the
    contradictory "+∞ + 🏆" a Black player saw when winning by
    timeout/resignation. Review eval-bar WDL now swaps W/L for a Black
    player (player-perspective labels, "W" = the player's win) AND gains a
    `if(_rt>0)` guard against `wdl 0 0 0` → NaN% (the main eval bar already
    had the guard). posDesc/posEmoji already received player-POV evP —
    unchanged. Eval trend chart stays White-POV (positive = White) by
    design — unchanged.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _formatEvalDelta colour is now player-perspective
    (green when the change favours the player; the displayed numeric delta
    stays White-POV to match the adjacent score). Mate-transition colouring
    (→# / escape) likewise player-perspective. Main eval-bar WDL swaps W/L
    for a Black player (player-perspective labels). _sfEval / _sfMateDistance
    stay White-POV (converted in onEngineEval) — unchanged. PGN-export WDL
    (pgn-standard.js) intentionally stays White-POV — unchanged.
