v1.2.3 round-18 (2026.7.17) — Chess960 PGN [FEN] bug fix + 7-agent line-by-line review:
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — bug-fix round).
  - ui-gameflow.js (GPL v3): MAIN BUG FIX — a newly started Chess960 game's
    PGN recorded the CURRENT position in its [FEN] tag instead of the
    INITIAL position. Root cause: _startGameImpl() assigned _setupFEN BEFORE
    _resetGameUIState(), which centrally nulls _setupFEN (silently
    re-breaking the v1.0.8 fix). Fixed by capturing the setup FEN in a
    local variable (_newGameInitialFEN) and assigning _setupFEN AFTER the
    reset (mirroring importPGN/_applyImportedFEN); reviewBaseState
    assignment likewise moved after the reset; the now-redundant manual
    state clears at the top of _startGameImpl removed.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _buildPGNString startFEN fallback uses
    stateHistory[0] (the game's TRUE initial position) when _setupFEN is
    unavailable for a Chess960 game; PlyCount counts actual half-moves
    (the intentional null placeholder for black-to-move starts no longer
    over-counts by 1); onBestMove discards the bestmove when the game is
    already over (gameOver guard) and the validation-failure auto-retry
    now actually fires (2 sites — the timer callback guards on
    isAIThinking, which the branch had just cleared, so the promised
    retry never ran; now an immediate retry, _aiRetryCount cap 3); engine
    variation numbering applies the _importedStartMoveNum offset (3 sites,
    same class as the round-13 tablebase.js fix); export list gains
    generateFEN/uciToCoords/_esc (defined in-module, previously listed by
    game-logic.js); removed the unused moveNum destructure in
    _processDeferredVariations.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): render() no longer resets _animRetryCount early (the
    >10-retries stuck-animation force-clear was dead code — guard
    restored); _resetGameUIState terminates any in-flight analyze-all
    batch (mirrors exitReview: _reviewAnalyzeAllActive, safety timer,
    _evalRequestBatchGen, _endEvalDeepBatchIfActive) and clears
    _pendingOpenStats; _replayMovesToState skips the intentional null
    placeholder of black-to-move games instead of aborting (visual
    annotations worked again for black-to-move games); reviewGoTo
    cache-hit path also restores _sfSeldepth (parity with the 6-field
    restore); SP-ID input keeps focus across keystroke-triggered
    re-renders (id=spidInput + _spidEditing flag + _postRenderFinalize
    restore, mirroring the ECO search box's _ecoSearchFocused mechanism);
    tablebase API unknown-category fallback HTML-escaped
    before entering innerHTML (same XSS threat model as the v1.0.8 PHASE
    30 _best.uci escaping); review-mode render skips the main-board
    control map (🌈 heatmap — main and review boards previously shared
    cachedCtrlKey/cachedCtrlMap and ping-ponged, forcing 2 full
    getCtrlMap() recomputes per render); cleanup: duplicate resets of 5
    variables removed from _resetGameUIState, export list gains posDesc
    (defined in-module).
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3): _validateSetupEpMark now requires both the
    skipped square AND the pawn's origin square to be empty (new i18n key
    setup_ep_err_blocked, zh+en); doAIMove tablebase path requires the
    live board to BE the saved board (gameState.board===_tbSavedBoard) so
    a TB move is never injected into a different game after an in-flight
    position change (falls through to the Stockfish path); export list
    drops the 4 foreign symbols generateFEN/uciToCoords/_esc (now
    exported by ai-bridge.js) and posDesc (now exported by ui.js).
  - tablebase.js (GPL v3): _parsePGN annotation-scan character class now
    includes '0' — digit-style 0-0/0-0-0 castling is counted, so trailing
    [%eval]/[%csl]/[%cal]/comment annotations no longer shift by one move;
    a Chess960 PGN without a [FEN] tag now clears the stale gameSPID.
  - pgn-standard.js (GPL v3): parseStandardPGN skips a stray close-brace
    (defensive infinite-loop fix; the function currently has no call
    sites).
  - worker-pool.js (GPL v3): PGN tokenizer header-strip regex now consumes
    the closing \] in BOTH the worker-side (template-literal, keeps
    double-escaping) and sync-side mirror copies.
  - index.html.tpl (GPL v3): invalid CSS contain-intrinsic-size:auto fixed
    to "auto 300px" (Chromium was dropping the whole declaration);
    removed the ineffective frame-ancestors directive from the CSP <meta>
    (frame-ancestors is only honored as an HTTP header).
  - chess.html: rebuilt from the updated modules + template (22,379 lines,
    1,346,688 bytes). See src/main/assets/README.license.
  - License classification: all files retain their existing classification.

v1.2.3 round-17 (2026.7.17) — SonarCloud high-priority cleanup + God Class refactor (ui split):
  - Version: versionCode=123, versionName="1.2.3" (unchanged — bug-fix round).
  - ui-gameflow.js (GPL v3): NEW FILE (313 lines) — God Class refactor:
    game start (startGame/_startGameImpl) + the game-clock subsystem
    (initGameClocks/_tickGameClock/_onGameClockExpired/recordMoveEnd/
    formatClock/_updateClockDisplay) extracted from ui.js. All functions
    moved verbatim; same global-scope module pattern (hoisted top-level
    function declarations, no top-level executable code moved — no
    TDZ/load-order change).
  - ui-interactions.js (GPL v3): NEW FILE (1,438 lines) — God Class refactor:
    board click handling (sqClick/setupClick/_getCastlingRookForClick), move
    execution & undo/redo (executeMove/_clearAnimationState/undoMove/redoMove),
    toolbar actions (flipBoard/quickFreeOpening/toggleSound/doPromotion/
    getHint/setDifficultyLevel), setup-mode entry/exit (toggleSetup/exitSetup/
    _exitSetupImpl/undoSetupClick/redoSetupClick), PGN-save prompt chain
    (_withPGNSaveCheck/_savePGNYes/_savePGNNo/_savePGNCancel), back-press
    routing (handleBackPress), import wrappers (_doPastePGN/
    _importFENWithSaveCheck/_importPGNFileWithSaveCheck), player rename &
    stats-import prompt (_renameHumanPlayer/_showStatsImportBackPrompt),
    resign (_resignGame) — all extracted from ui.js verbatim.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): 8,475 → 6,761 lines (-20%). Beyond the extraction:
    (1) S2703 REAL BUG FIX — _refreshEvalTrendChart referenced `_trendH`,
    a const LOCAL to _renderReviewMode (undeclared global in this scope):
    latent ReferenceError whenever the chart container had zero layout
    height. Fixed by extracting the shared height formula into a new
    top-level _computeTrendChartHeight() helper used by both call sites.
    The PDF's other ~121 claimed S2703 implicit globals were verified false
    positives (all variables are properly let/const-declared; ECO_OPENINGS
    is an intentional lazy window property; gameEvent/gameSite are
    typeof-guarded optional externals). (2) S7740 — 9 `const self = this`
    closures converted to arrow functions (4 onended + 5 forEach in
    ChessAudioEngine). (3) S7741 — typeof-undefined comparisons converted
    to direct !== undefined ONLY where the variable is declared in the same
    module (6 sites: reviewMode/reviewStep/moveRecords/gameClockTimerId×2);
    cross-module typeof guards intentionally retained (round-11 design:
    resilience against single-module load failure), as are guards on
    externally-injected globals (AndroidBridge, gameEvent, gameSite).
  - All JS modules: S7773 — 99 global isNaN/parseInt/isFinite calls converted
    to Number.isNaN/Number.parseInt/Number.isFinite across ai-bridge.js,
    game-logic.js, pgn-standard.js, tablebase.js, ui.js (each call site
    individually verified to pass number-typed arguments, so the dropped
    string-coercion of the globals is behavior-preserving).
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): S7761 — setAttribute('data-theme') →
    documentElement.dataset.theme. S7741 — 3 same-module typeof conversions
    (_reviewEvalRequestedStep, playerWhite, playerBlack).
  - chess960.js (AGPL v3): S7767 — 3 `|0` truncations → Math.trunc
    (identical for the spid ∈ [0,959] domain).
  - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): S8786 — nested-quantifier move-number regex
    /\d+\.+(\d+\.+)*/g simplified to /\d+\.+/g in BOTH the worker-side
    (template-literal, keeps double-escaping) and sync-side copies; the
    (\d+\.+)* tail was redundant for the replace use-case. Pipeline-level
    equivalence (incl. the subsequent \s+→' ' normalization) verified on
    7 test inputs incl. adversarial ones.
  - S7781: 3 string-first-arg .replace calls converted to .replaceAll where
    global replacement is intended (ui.js i18n placeholders N1/N2/{count}/
    {total}/{filter}); printf-style SEQUENTIAL %d substitution in stats.html
    intentionally left as .replace (replaceAll would break it).
  - build-chess.py: MODULES list now includes ui-gameflow.js and
    ui-interactions.js before ui.js (concatenation order safe — hoisting).
  - License classification: new files inherit ui.js's GPL v3 (derived from
    DroidFish-referencing code); all other files retain their classification.

