v1.2.1 (2026.7.13, eighth-pass refinement — round-8 review):
  - Version: versionCode=121, versionName="1.2.1" (unchanged — same-version refinement).
  - state-store.js (AGPL v3): Fixed TDZ (Temporal Dead Zone) white-screen bug
    introduced in round-7. The round-7 _deepClone() hardening added
    `const DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH = 64;` AFTER the IIFE-top initialization call
    `let _state = _deepClone(_initialState);`. Since `const` declarations do
    NOT hoist like `var` (they are in TDZ until their declaration line
    executes), the function body's reference to DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH triggered
    `ReferenceError: Cannot access 'DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH' before
    initialization`. The state-store module initialization crashed, every
    dependent module (ui.js, ai-bridge.js, etc.) failed to load, and the
    WebView rendered only <body>'s background color. Fix: moved the const
    declaration to IIFE-top, BEFORE the `_state` initialization, with a
    documentation comment explaining the TDZ trap.
  - ai-bridge.js, chess960.js, eco-data.js, game-logic.js, pgn-standard.js,
    tablebase.js, ui.js, worker-pool.js, index.html.tpl: no changes (round-7
    state preserved; only state-store.js touched in this pass).
  - chess.html: rebuilt via build-chess.py to pick up the state-store.js fix.
  - All 9 JS modules pass `node --check`.
  - License classification: all files retain existing classification.
    state-store.js remains AGPL v3 (original work, not DroidFish-derived).

v1.2.1 (2026.7.13, eighth-pass refinement — round-8 review):
  - Version: versionCode=121, versionName="1.2.1" (unchanged — same-version refinement).
  - state-store.js (AGPL v3): Fixed TDZ (Temporal Dead Zone) white-screen bug
    introduced in round-7. The round-7 _deepClone() hardening added
    `const DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH = 64;` AFTER the IIFE-top initialization call
    `let _state = _deepClone(_initialState);`. Since `const` declarations do
    NOT hoist like `var` (they are in TDZ until their declaration line
    executes), the function body's reference to DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH triggered
    `ReferenceError: Cannot access 'DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH' before
    initialization`. The state-store module initialization crashed, every
    dependent module (ui.js, ai-bridge.js, etc.) failed to load, and the
    WebView rendered only <body>'s background color. Fix: moved the const
    declaration to IIFE-top, BEFORE the `_state` initialization, with a
    documentation comment explaining the TDZ trap.
  - ai-bridge.js, chess960.js, eco-data.js, game-logic.js, pgn-standard.js,
    tablebase.js, ui.js, worker-pool.js, index.html.tpl: no changes (round-7
    state preserved; only state-store.js touched in this pass).
  - chess.html: rebuilt via build-chess.py to pick up the state-store.js fix.
  - All 9 JS modules pass `node --check`.
  - License classification: all files retain existing classification.
    state-store.js remains AGPL v3 (original work, not DroidFish-derived).

v1.2.1 (2026.7.13, seventh-pass refinement — round-7 review):
  - Version: versionCode=121, versionName="1.2.1" (unchanged — same-version refinement).
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _buildPGNString() no longer filters visual
    annotations by `imported` flag — reverted Phase 62 design. All
    visual annotations now export based solely on includeAnnotations
    parameter. setConfigElo() clamp range 500-3200 → 500-3500 to match
    Java side (EngineConfigHelper canonical range). onBestMove() now
    probes gameStatus() when engine returns (none)/0000 — terminal
    positions (checkmate/stalemate) apply game-over immediately instead
    of retrying for up to 18 minutes (3 × 360s safety timer).
    openStatsPage() comment updated to note the Phase 62 revert.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): removed three unreachable `typeof _requestBatchEval
    === 'function'` checks (SonarCloud B02/B03, javascript:S2589) —
    _requestBatchEval is always exported by ai-bridge.js. Simplified
    `r !== null && r !== undefined` to `r != null` (SonarCloud B04,
    javascript:S3403) in _withPGNSaveCheck.
  - index.html.tpl (GPL v3): removed redundant `flex-shrink:0` declaration
    before `flex:0 0 auto` in .dlg-btns rule (SonarCloud B01, css:S4652).
    The shorthand `flex:0 0 auto` already sets flex-shrink:0.
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3): secureRandomInt() no longer falls back to
    Math.random() when crypto API is unavailable — now returns 0 + logs
    console.error (fail-safe). Mirrors randomSPID() pattern in chess960.js
    (which returns SP-ID 518). Math.random() is a predictable PRNG;
    using it for Chess960 SP-ID or ECO opening-book picks would defeat
    cryptographic randomization.
  - state-store.js (AGPL v3): _deepClone() now uses
    `new RegExp(obj.source, obj.flags)` instead of `new RegExp(obj)`
    (eliminates Semgrep detect-non-literal-regexp FP). Added depth guard
    (DEEP_CLONE_MAX_DEPTH=64) to prevent stack overflow on pathological
    deeply-nested or cyclic inputs.
  - chess960.js, pgn-standard.js, worker-pool.js, tablebase.js, eco-data.js:
    no changes (verified clean in round-5; no new findings in round-7).
  - License classification: all files retain existing classification.
    state-store.js remains AGPL v3 (original work, not DroidFish-derived).

v1.2.1 (2026.7.13, sixth-pass refinement — round-6 review):
  - Version: versionCode=121, versionName="1.2.1" (unchanged — same-version refinement).
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): openStatsPage() now collects all
    _visualAnnotationsCache entries (skipping the _initial key) into a vaData
    object and includes it in the JSON payload as `visualAnnotations`. This
    gives the stats page access to ALL annotation entries (both imported=true
    and imported=false), not just the imported ones that _buildPGNString
    exports to PGN text. Fixes user-reported bug where the stats page's visual
    annotations section was silently hidden for all newly-played games.
