v1.2.1 (2026.7.13, fourth-pass refinement — round-4 cleanup, dead-module purge):
  - Version: versionCode=121, versionName="1.2.1" (unchanged — same-version refinement).
  - Deleted ui-audio.js (GPL v3): the inline ChessAudioEngine in ui.js already
    owns the AudioContext, gain, and enabled state. UIAudio's setEnabled /
    unlockAudio were called from try-catch wrappers that no-op'd when undefined;
    its separate _volume / _enabled state could drift out of sync with
    ChessAudioEngine. Pure dead code.
  - Deleted ui-board.js (GPL v3): provided getSquareBg / getSquareName /
    addReviewBoardCoords helpers, but the inline ui.js board rendering uses
    the OPPOSITE rank convention (rr=0 → rank 8, not rank 1). The two could
    never be unified without rewriting one of them. Never called from the
    hot path — only typeof guards in ai-bridge.js.
  - Deleted ui-review.js (GPL v3): provided classifyMove / annotateMove
    helpers, but used a different classification taxonomy (best/excellent/
    good/ok/inaccuracy/mistake/blunder) than the inline _classifyMove in
    ui.js (brilliant/great/good/book/blunder/mistake/inaccuracy). Direct
    replacement would silently change review annotations.
  - Deleted ui-toolbar.js (GPL v3): provided switchLanguage / BTN_ID, but
    switchLanguage just re-implemented toggleLang's persistence + dispatch
    logic, and BTN_ID was never read. Pure redundancy.
  - build-chess.py: module list reduced 13 → 9 (removed the four ui-*.js
    modules above).
  - ui.js: removed UIAudio.unlockAudio() call in _unlockAudio; removed
    UIAudio.setEnabled(soundOn) call in toggleSound. Both were wrapped in
    try-catch and no-op'd when undefined; ChessAudioEngine is the sole
    audio state owner.
  - game-logic.js: removed UIToolbar.switchLanguage(_lang) call in
    toggleLang. toggleLang already dispatches SET_LANG to the Store,
    persists to localStorage, and notifies AndroidBridge — UIToolbar was
    a redundant third channel.
  - ai-bridge.js: removed window.MessageBus._onEvent JS stub and the
    four typeof-guarded module-activation checks (UIAudio.isEnabled /
    UIBoard.getSquareName / UIReview.classifyMove / UIToolbar.BTN_ID).
    The stub only console.log'd events; the activation checks only verified
    that the now-deleted modules were loadable.
  - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ via build-chess.py.


