v1.1.2 Phase 72 (2026.7.12, same-version revision):
  - Version remains versionCode=112, versionName="1.1.2".
  - ui.js (GPL v3): _reviewAnalyzeAdvance — fixed "false completion" bug
    after long-press priority eval. Previously, the completion check ONLY
    walked forward from _reviewAnalyzeStep+1; when a priority eval jumped
    ahead (e.g., user long-pressed step 50 during a batch at step 5), the
    batch evaluated step 50, then the forward walk reached _lastStep and
    reported "all analysis complete" — even though steps 0-49 were still
    uncached. Fix: when the forward walk finds nothing, scan the ENTIRE
    range [0.._lastStep] for the lowest uncached step and resume the batch
    from there. The forward-only fast-path is preserved for the common
    (no-priority) case; the full-range scan is the source of truth for
    completion.
  - No new modules; build-order unchanged. Re-run python3 build-chess.py.

v1.1.2 Phase 71 (2026.7.11, same-version revision):
  - Version remains versionCode=112, versionName="1.1.2".
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): uciToCoords — when rewriting Chess960 castling
    destination (king-captures-rook UCI notation), now attaches castle=
    'kingside'/'queenside' to result.to so _castleSide's primary path catches
    it. Fixes 0-distance king castling (king already on g1/c1) where the
    previous distance-based fallback rejected the move and makeMv nulled
    the king.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): executeMove — check to.castle as the PRIMARY source for
    the castle flag (covers AI moves where legalMvs is empty). The legalMvs
    lookup is now the fallback.
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3): _castleSide — added explicit 0-distance branch
    (defense-in-depth: when _is960 && _dist===0 && _cr[side], return
    'kingside'/'queenside'). secureRandomInt — crypto undefined guard (falls
    back to Math.random). moveAlg — setupMode typeof guard (was bare
    if(setupMode)). makeMv/makeMvInPlace/Zobrist — en-passant cr bounds
    check via inB() (defense-in-depth).
  - chess960.js (AGPL v3): toShredderCastling — board null/undefined guard
    (mirrors parseShredderCastling's defensive pattern).
  - pgn-standard.js (GPL v3): sevenTagRoster/composePGN — null/undefined
    params guard (defense-in-depth).
  - worker-pool.js (GPL v3): _createWorker — 3-strike transient-failure
    counter; no longer permanently disables the pool on a single OOM.
  - No new modules; build-order unchanged. Re-run python3 build-chess.py.

