v1.1.0 Phase 58: every-5-moves PGN {} eval annotation + StockfishNative concurrency fixes.
  - pgn-standard.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): New formatEvalAnnotation(cached)
    function builds a human-readable, White-perspective eval annotation for the
    every-5-moves PGN {} comment. Format mirrors the eval bar:
      "<desc> (<score>) D<depth> SD<seldepth> (<W%>W/<D%>D/<L%>L)"
    e.g. "均势 (-0.10) D22 SD34 (1%W/96%D/3%L)" (Chinese) /
         "Equal (-0.10) D22 SD34 (1%W/96%D/3%L)" (English).
    Language auto-selected via T() reading the global _lang variable. Missing
    components (depth, WDL) gracefully omitted; zero-sum WDL guarded against
    divide-by-zero. Mate uses "#+N"/"#-N" + "White mates"/"Black mates" label.
    New _pgnWhitePerspectiveLabel(ev) helper maps White-POV centipawn eval to
    White-perspective label (mirrors posDesc() thresholds from ui.js but
    returns White-POV strings).
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): New pgn_* i18n keys for White-
    perspective eval labels: pgn_white_winning, pgn_white_huge_adv,
    pgn_white_advantage, pgn_white_slight_adv, pgn_equal, pgn_black_slight_adv,
    pgn_black_advantage, pgn_black_huge_adv, pgn_black_winning, pgn_mate_white,
    pgn_mate_black.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): In _buildPGNString, at moves 5,
    10, 15, 20, ... (i.e. _moveNum % 5 === 0), append the formatEvalAnnotation
    fragment to the PGN {} comment. Placed AFTER [%eval] tag (structured tags
    stay first per PGN spec) and BEFORE free-text/resign/timeout annotations.

v1.1.0 Phase 57+: code-review-driven preventive hardening.
  - pgn-standard.js (parseStandardPGN): Replaced the single-line PGN tag-stripping
    regex `/^\[[\s\S]*?\]/gm` (which only matched the FIRST tag when all tags +
    movetext were on ONE line, due to the `^` anchor with `gm` flags only matching
    the very start of the string) with the format-strict, unanchored
    `/\[[A-Za-z]\w*\s+"[^"]*"\]/g`. The new pattern requires the canonical PGN
    tag shape (key + whitespace + double-quoted value), so movetext comments
    like `[Nf3]` (no quotes, no key-value shape) are never false-positive stripped.
    parseStandardPGN is currently NOT on the main code path (the main parser is
    tablebase.js _parsePGN, fixed in Phase 52); this is a preventive fix. (GPL v3,
    DroidFish-derived.)
  - chess960.js (isChess960CastlingLegal): King-position lookup now reads the
    state's cached `s.wk` / `s.bk` fields directly (maintained by syncHash() and
    cloneS() in game-logic.js), consistent with how other king-position lookups
    are done throughout the codebase. A defensive board-scan fallback is retained
    for states that may not have the cache populated (e.g. hand-built test
    harness states). (AGPL v3, original.)
  - ai-bridge.js (WDL display): Added `if(total>0)` guard before dividing
    _sfWdlW/_sfWdlD/_sfWdlL by their sum to compute WDL percentages. Without
    this guard, if the engine emitted `wdl 0 0 0` in a pathological position,
    the division would produce NaN/Infinity in the WDL percentage string.
    (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived.)

v1.1.0 Phase 57: portrait review move-list scroll positioning + visual-annotation cache residue fix.
  - ui.js (render): Replaced the Phase 56 _rAct.offsetTop-based scroll calculation
    with a getBoundingClientRect()-based calculation. The Phase 56 fix used
    offsetTop, which returns distance to offsetParent (.review-overlay, which is
    position:fixed) — NOT to _rList (.review-moves has no position set). In
    landscape the error was small (~24px header), but in portrait the error
    included the board's full height (256-320px), causing the active move to be
    clamped to scrollHeight-clientHeight (scrolled to bottom) and not centered.
    The new calculation: _actTop = (_actRect.top - _listRect.top) + _rList.scrollTop
    gives the active move's position within _rList's full content (including
    scrolled-away portion), regardless of orientation, layout, or offsetParent
    chain. Defensive fallback to offsetTop preserved.
  - ui.js (enterReview): Added _visualAnnotationsCache.delete('_initial') at entry.
    The '_initial' key was previously never cleared between review sessions
    (only _resetGameUIState clears it, called by new-game/import/setup/FEN). If
    the user re-entered review without one of those entry points in between
    (e.g., continued playing the same game and re-entered review), the stale
    '_initial' cache persisted and wrong annotations rendered at step 0.
    Numeric keys (0..N-1) are deliberately preserved — they were computed during
    play and are still valid.
  - ui.js (_computeInitialPositionAnnotations): Now reads reviewStates[0].state
    (the actual initial position shown at reviewStep=0) instead of gameState
    (the LIVE mid-game state). Previously, the '_initial' cache was populated
    with annotations computed for the mid-game position (e.g., threats to a
    queen on d4), but the board at step 0 shows the initial position (queen on
    d1). The mismatch caused stale, irrelevant annotations at step 0 — perceived
    by the user as "残留旧对局的过时视觉注解". Fallback chain:
    reviewStates[0].state → reviewBaseState → gameState (defensive).
    Chess960: reviewStates[0].state has the Chess960 starting position (with
    spid set), so getCtrlMap/attacked compute annotations correctly for both
    standard chess and Chess960.

v1.1.0 Phase 56: landscape review nav-button scroll-to-top fix + PGN timeout annotation + first-move timing sync + UCI command ordering refinement.
  - ui.js: Replaced scrollIntoView({block:'center'}) on the active review move with
    manual scrollTop computation on the inner .review-moves container only. The old
    scrollIntoView scrolled ALL ancestors including the outer .review-body, causing
    the page to jump back to top when nav buttons at the bottom were clicked in
    landscape review mode.
  - ui.js: Added _turnStartTime=Date.now() and gameClocks=null to _resetGameUIState().
    _turnStartTime was never reset at game-start entry points, so the first move's
    [%emt]/{Xs} annotation included time since the previous game's last move (could
    be hours/days). gameClocks was not nulled at non-dialog entry points (FEN/PGN
    import, setup-complete), causing stale clock state to leak.
  - ai-bridge.js: Added [Termination "Time forfeit"] tag and {<color> wins by timeout}
    comment for games ending by timeout. Previously only resignation had these
    annotations; timeout games were missing the Termination tag and last-move comment.
  - StockfishNative.java (engineGoTimed, engineGoInternal): Moved setGameDifficulty's
    setoption commands to BEFORE position fen (previously between position fen and go)
    for cleaner UCI ordering. Verified Chess960+TimeControl UCI sequence is correct:
    setoption UCI_Chess960 → isready → ucinewgame → isready → position fen (Shredder)
    → go wtime/btime/winc/binc.

v1.1.0 Phase 55: Chess960 castling rook-loss fix in stats.html + game-logic.js _castleSide fallback.
  - game-logic.js: _castleSide() fallback castling detection replaced _destEmpty with
    _destValid. In Chess960, the king's destination (c1 for O-O-O, g1 for O-O) CAN be
    the participating rook's source square (e.g. king on d1, rook on c1: O-O-O puts
    king on c1 = rook's source). The old _destEmpty check rejected this case, causing
    the king to "self-capture" the rook and silently lose it. The corrected check
    allows the destination to be empty OR contain a same-color rook (the participating
    castling rook, which moves away). Corrected the incorrect Phase 49 comment that
    claimed "Castling destination squares are ALWAYS empty". Standard chess is
    unaffected (rook always on a1/h1, king dest c1/g1 always empty).

v1.1.0 Phase 54: custom slider for pixel-perfect chart alignment + move-list scroll-into-view fix + executeMove async-callback try-catch + audio-engine partial-init reset + engine heartbeat all-callbacks fix + MultiPV secondary-variation divergence fix + PGN cascade-skip threshold increase + render retry-loop guard.
  - ui.js + index.html.tpl: replaced native <input type="range"> visual with
    custom track/fill/thumb divs. Slider wrapper has IDENTICAL CSS to chart
    container (border:1px, padding:2px, box-sizing:border-box, width:100%).
    Thumb center positioned via CSS calc(3px + ratio * (100% - 6px)) matching
    chart data points at viewBox x=3 and x=width-3. Native input is now a
    transparent overlay (opacity:0) for touch/drag/keyboard interaction.
  - ui.js: move-list scroll-into-view now only scrolls when active move is NOT
    fully visible (block:'nearest'). _lastReviewStepScrolled moved inside rAF
    callback so failed scrolls retry on next render.
  - ui.js: executeMove setTimeout callback wrapped in try-catch.
  - ui.js: ChessAudioEngine.init() resets ALL fields on partial-failure
    (ctx, master, compressor, reverb, reverbGain, dryGain, _noiseBuf).
    setEnabled/setVolume guard both master AND ctx.
  - ui.js: render() retry loop on animationInProgress now has _animRetryCount
    guard (max 10 retries = 2s, then force-clear and render).
  - ai-bridge.js: _lastEngineCallbackTime updated in onEngineProgress,
    onBestMove, onHintMove, onPonderProgress (was only in onEngineEval).
    Prevents false-positive engine restart during long AI thinks.
  - ai-bridge.js: _checkPVDivergenceSANs now distinguishes secondary
    variations (alternative to move at fromMoveIdx) from mainline
    continuations. Secondary: actualIdx = fromMoveIdx + vi. Mainline:
    actualIdx = fromMoveIdx + 1 + vi (previous behavior).
  - tablebase.js: _parsePGN cascade-skip threshold increased from 5 to
    Math.max(15, mainTokens.length * 0.1) — tolerates localized PGN
    corruption without dropping the rest of the game.
  - Revision 2 (2026.7.4): chart left/right padding 3→0 (first/last data
    points at x=0 and x=width, edge-to-edge). Slider thumb center
    calc(3px + ratio * (100% - 6px)) → calc(ratio * 100%). Slider base
    track and fill left:3px → left:0. Slider container overflow:visible
    so 6px thumb overflows 3px at min/max. Both chart and slider now
    fill the full width.
  - Revision 3 (2026.7.4): true edge-to-edge. Root cause: chart CONTAINER
    had padding:2px (inline style), so SVG content-box was 3px inset
    from outer edge (1px border + 2px padding). Slider wrapper also had
    padding:2px. Fix: chart container inline padding 2px→0, slider
    wrapper CSS padding 2px→0 (both keep border:1px). Now SVG fills
    content-box = border-box minus 1px border — data points at inner
    edge of 1px border, visually edge-to-edge. _trendW measurement:
    clientWidth (no -4, since padding=0). Slider labels get
    padding:2px 3px. Also fix move-list scroll-into-view: (1) skip
    .review-moves scroll restore when reviewStep changed (was fighting
    with scroll-into-view); (2) always center active move when step
    changed (removed "already visible" skip that left move at edge).
  - Revision 4 (2026.7.4): move-list scroll complete rebuild + thumb/
    chart circle alignment + no clipping.
    (1) Move-list scroll: discarded old save/restore mechanism for
    .review-moves entirely. Removed .review-moves from _savedContainerScrolls
    selectors. After EVERY render(), ALWAYS center active move — no
    _lastReviewStepScrolled guard, no "already visible" check.
    (2) Thumb diameter = marker circle: chart current-position marker
    is SVG r=4 + stroke-width=1.5 → outer diameter 9.5px. Slider thumb
    6px → 10px. Slider container 18px → 20px. Native input thumb
    18px → 20px.
    (3) No clipping: chart container overflow hidden → visible (inline
    + CSS). Data point circles (r=2.75) at edges fully visible (overflow
    into .review-bottom's 6px padding). Slider thumb (10px) overflows
    5px at min/max — accommodated by 6px padding. .rv-slider-wrap
    explicit overflow:visible.
  - Revision 5 (2026.7.4): eval label color/contrast + global-mode label
    removal + strict 9.5px thumb + portrait clipping fix + move-list
    scroll block:'nearest'.
    (1) Eval label color: added --chart-label CSS var (#f5e6c8 dark,
    #2c2c34 light). Local-mode eval labels use _C_LABEL for high
    contrast. Mate labels keep _C_CRIT (gold).
    (2) Label edge clipping: X-clamp labels to [estHalfW, width-estHalfW]
    (estHalfW = fontSize * label.length * 0.32).
    (3) Global-mode label removal: removed "last endpoint checkmate
    distance display" block. Global mode purely visual.
    (4) Strict 9.5px thumb: 7.5px width/height + 1px border = 9.5px
    outer, exactly matching chart marker (r=4 + stroke 1.5 → 9.5px).
    (5) Portrait clipping: .review-bottom padding 6px → 8px (> 4.75px
    overflow). Explicit overflow:visible.
    (6) Move-list scroll: replaced "always center" (broke scrolling)
    with block:'nearest' — only scroll if active NOT fully visible
    (top-align if above, bottom-align if below). Restored
    _lastReviewStepScrolled guard for toggles.
  - Revision 6 (2026.7.4): native scrollIntoView + symmetric edge clipping.
    (1) Move-list scroll: replaced manual block:'nearest' calc (had
    virtual-list spacer height errors) with native
    scrollIntoView({block:'nearest', behavior:'auto'}). Precise jump.
    (2) Symmetric edge clipping: chart container overflow visible → hidden
    (inline + CSS). Slider container overflow visible → hidden. Both
    chart data point circles (r=2.75) and slider thumb (9.5px) clipped
    symmetrically at edges. Centers align at edge, clipped halves are
    mirror images → strict pixel-level alignment.
  - Revision 7 (2026.7.4): nav-button scroll pull-back fix + SVG
    overflow:hidden.
    (1) Nav-button scroll: root cause — render() resets .review-moves
    scrollTop to 0, scrollIntoView jumps from 0. Fix: _savedReviewMovesScroll
    saves scrollTop before innerHTML, restores after (clamped). Restore
    BEFORE scrollIntoView — list returns to user position, then
    scrollIntoView only scrolls if active not visible.
    (2) SVG edge clipping: SVG overflow defaults to visible in some
    WebViews. preserveAspectRatio scaling in landscape moved data points
    inward, escaping container clip. Fix: added overflow:hidden to SVG
    inline style. SVG now clips content outside viewBox — consistent
    clipping regardless of scaling or selection state.
  - Revision 8 (2026.7.4): SVG slice + 100x100 viewBox + scroll-restore
    only when step unchanged.
    (1) SVG: replaced pixel viewBox + "meet" with fixed viewBox="0 0 100
    100" + preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice". "slice" scales to COVER
    container — no centering gaps. All coords in 0-100 space (r 2.5→1.6,
    marker r 4→2.5, stroke/font scaled). _buildEvalTrendSVG no params.
    Removed _trendW measurement.
    (2) Scroll-restore: only restore _savedReviewMovesScroll when
    reviewStep did NOT change. When changed, virtual list window
    recomputed → old scrollTop meaningless → skip restore, let
    scrollIntoView handle from 0. Eliminates pull-back.
  - Revision 9 (2026.7.4): eliminate post-scrollIntoView pull-back.
    Two async ops fired AFTER scrollIntoView, resetting scroll:
    (1) Measurement rAF: on first virtual render, rAF measured
    avgRowH, REBUILT innerHTML with accurate spacers, restored
    _oldScrollTop (captured AFTER scrollIntoView, new DOM different
    geometry → wrong position → pull-back). Fix: removed innerHTML
    rebuild + restore — only record avgRowH, used on NEXT render.
    (2) Scroll-driven refresh: scrollIntoView fires scroll event →
    _refreshReviewMovesOnly (80ms debounce) → rebuilds innerHTML →
    restores old scrollTop on new DOM → pull-back. Fix: added
    _suppressScrollRefresh guard — set true when reviewStep changed,
    makes _refreshReviewMovesOnly early-return. Cleared after 300ms.
  - Revision 10 (2026.7.4): skip scrollIntoView during Analyze All +
    fix chart display.
    (1) Periodic pull-back: during Analyze All,
    _reviewAnalyzeAdvance() changes reviewStep every 1-5s, calls
    render() → scrollIntoView pulls list to analyzed step. Fix: when
    _reviewAnalyzeAllActive is true, skip scrollIntoView — preserve
    user scroll. Runs once when analyze-all completes.
    (2) Chart display: "xMidYMid slice" + viewBox 100x100 caused
    vertical cropping in wide-short containers (portrait ~350x100:
    scale=3.5, content 294px tall, container 100px → 194px cropped).
    Fix: preserveAspectRatio "xMidYMid slice" → "none". Stretches to
    FILL independently in X/Y — no cropping. Slight distortion but
    ALL content visible.
  - Revision 11 (2026.7.4): dynamic viewBox + always-restore scrollTop.
    (1) Chart: user rejected "none". First-principles: "slice" crops
    when viewBox aspect ≠ container aspect. Solution: DYNAMIC viewBox
    "0 0 <width> <height>" where width = measured container clientWidth,
    height = _trendH. Aspect matches → "slice" 1:1 → NO cropping, NO
    distortion. Kept "xMidYMid slice". Coords back to pixel space.
    (2) Scroll: ALWAYS save/restore .review-moves scrollTop across DOM
    rebuild. Restore BEFORE scrollIntoView. scrollIntoView only when
    reviewStep changed AND analyze-all NOT active. No pull-back.
  - Revision 12 (2026.7.4): eliminate periodic pull-back by not calling
    render() during Analyze All advance. Root cause:
    _reviewAnalyzeAdvance() called render() every step (1-5s), rebuilding
    DOM + forcing virtual-list window recompute — discarded user's scroll
    window. Fix: removed render() from advance. Now ONLY calls
    _updateAllEvalDisplays() + _updateReviewAnalyzeBtn() +
    requestEngineEval() (no DOM rebuild). Full render() once when
    analyze-all completes (reviewGoTo(returnStep)). No DOM rebuild =
    no scroll disruption.
  - Revision 13 (2026.7.4): fix virtual-list window recompute discarding
    user's scroll position (>90 steps reverts). Root cause: window
    recompute condition had "!measured" which forced recompute on EVERY
    render until avgRowH measured. When user scrolled past move 90 then
    triggered any render, window snapped back to reviewStep (≤90).
    Fix: removed "!measured" condition. Window recomputed ONLY when
    first virtual render or reviewStep changed. Scroll-based window
    preserved across renders.
  - Revision 14 (2026.7.4): DISABLE virtual list entirely.
    RV_VIRTUAL_THRESHOLD=Infinity. All bugs caused by virtual list
    (can't scroll past 40, fast nav pull-back, selection lost, >90
    revert, periodic pull-back). Every move always in DOM. Simplified
    scrollIntoView: just scrollIntoView({block:'nearest'}) in double-rAF
    when reviewStep changed and analyze-all not active.
  - Revision 15 (2026.7.4): dead-code cleanup — removed ~145 lines of
    dead virtual-list code: _suppressScrollRefresh,
    _refreshReviewMovesOnly, _onReviewMovesScroll,
    _forceReviewWindowToStep, _computeVirtualWindow (dead functions);
    RV_OVERSCAN, RV_SCROLL_DEBOUNCE_MS (dead constants);
    _lastRenderReviewStep (dead variable); if(_rvVirtualState.enabled)
    branch in render() (dead branch); scroll-listener + avgRowH rAF
    block (dead post-render block); spacer rendering (dead branches).
    No runtime behavior change.
  - Revision 16 (2026.7.4): fix selection scrolled out of view at last
    step + enter review at step 0 + ⏮ two clicks.
    (1) block:'nearest' → block:'center' (active move centered, not at
    edge). Force _lastReviewStepScrolled=-2 in reviewGoTo so
    scrollIntoView fires even when step doesn't change (▶ at last step).
    (2) enterReview sets reviewStep=0 (was lastStep). Chart starts from
    step 0 with real data. ⏮ at step 0 works in one click.
  - Revision 17 (2026.7.4): fix review page scrolling to top on every
    nav button / move click. Root cause: render() rebuilds DOM,
    resetting scrollTop to 0. .review-moves restore was in rAF (too
    late — browser painted scrollTop=0 before rAF → visible jump).
    Fix: both .review-body and .review-moves scrollTop restores now
    SYNCHRONOUS after app.innerHTML=h, before browser paints.
  - Revision 18 (2026.7.4): fix board not refreshing during Analyze
    All + restore auto-select/jump. rev12 removed render() from
    _reviewAnalyzeAdvance() to fix scroll pull-back — but board/eval/
    move-list/chart never updated during analysis. Fix: restored
    render() — scroll pull-back now fixed by synchronous scrollTop
    restore (rev17). Force _lastReviewStepScrolled=-2 so
    scrollIntoView fires. User sees board update + active move centered.
  - Revision 19 (2026.7.4): final audit — remove stale analyze-all
    scroll guard (rev18 restored render, user wants scrollIntoView
    during analysis). Fix _savedReviewBodyScroll not cleared after
    restore (stale value caused spurious restore on next render).
  - Revision 20 (2026.7.4): fix stale engine variation data polluting
    new game after setup/import. _pendingEngineSANs, _pendingEnginePVs,
    _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult, _lastEngineVariation, reviewCritical
    indexed by moveRecords indices — new game reuses indices, stale data
    attaches to wrong moves. Fix: clear in _exitSetupImpl (ui.js),
    _applyImportedFEN + importPGN (tablebase.js).
  - Revision 21 (2026.7.4): final audit — also clear stale engine data
    in _startGameImpl (new game via dialog). Same index-reuse issue as
    rev20. Fix: added same clearing in _startGameImpl.
  - Revision 22 (2026.7.4): fix stats page Chess960 castling support.
    (1) buildSAN castling detection: abs(to-from)===2 → same logic as
    executeMove (home row, col 6/2, >=1 dist for 960, dest empty,
    right present). (2) fenToState: added Shredder-FEN castling
    notation parsing (file letters AHah). (3) gameVariant: sent in
    payload from openStatsPage (ai-bridge.js), received in stats.html,
    also detected from [Variant] header in parsePGN.

v1.1.0 Phase 53: green-arrow check-response + red-arrow discovered-check fix + king-position staleness fix + FEN-import state-pollution fix + exitSetup state-pollution fix + portrait/landscape review layout unification + stats visual-annotation cutoff + review progress-bar/eval-chart alignment (revised) + king-control-arrow legality filter + nav-button center-align.
  - ui.js _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations: green arrows redefined from "king
    escape path" to "check response path". Now uses legalMoves(postState, null)
    (single call) and filters for king-origin moves (m.from === oppKingPos) and
    capture-the-checker moves (m.to === checker position). Includes en passant
    captures; double check correctly excludes non-king captures. Fixes v1.0.9
    bug where arrows were drawn to squares the king couldn't legally move to.
    Chess960: legalMoves handles Chess960 castling (forbidden in check) and
    en passant identically to standard chess — no special-casing needed.
  - ui.js _updateArrows + _updateCtrlInfoPanel + _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations
    + _computeInitialPositionAnnotations: king-control-arrow legality filter.
    Arrows from a king's current square are suppressed when the target square
    is controlled by the opponent (king cannot legally move there). Applies
    to both player's and opponent's king. Filters king attackers in the
    threatByMover/threatByOpp/threatByWhite/threatByBlack maps, which also
    correctly filters yellow queen-threat and blue multi-threat arrows from
    a king.
  - ui.js _buildEvalTrendSVG: chart padding reduced 8→3 (left/right) so the
    first/last data points sit closer to the edges (at [3, width-3]).
  - ui.js _buildEvalTrendSVG caller: _trendW measured from existing
    .review-chart container's clientWidth on re-renders (was window-based
    estimate). Makes viewBox width == SVG actual width.
  - ui.js review slider HTML: wrapper has border:1px solid transparent +
    padding:2px + box-sizing:border-box, matching the chart container's
    effective horizontal layout exactly.
  - index.html.tpl: slider track gets margin:0 3px (matching chart padding)
    so the track spans [3, width-3] = first/last data points exactly. Thumb
    width 12px (= 2 × padding): at min value thumb LEFT edge at first point,
    at max value thumb RIGHT edge at last point. Both ::-webkit and ::-moz
    covered. .review-nav .btn gets justify-content:center (nav button text
    center-aligned). Title: "Regalia v1.0.9" → "Regalia v1.1.0".
  - game-logic.js: loading_title "Regalia v1.0.9" → "Regalia v1.1.0".
  - stats.html (sibling file, not in this directory): visual annotations desc
    + green_arrows label updated (escape path → check-response); added
    _slicePGNAtMove helper; visual annotations stats block now respects
    selected-move cutoff. See assets/README.license for details.
v1.0.9 Phase 52: PGN single-line parse fix + review "extra kings" fix + visual annotation variation-isolation fix + isCheck/isCastling import fix + eval-chart palette unified to blue-vs-red.
  - tablebase.js _parsePGN: tag-stripping regex /^\[[^\]]*\]/gm → /\[[A-Za-z]\w*\s+[^\]]+\]/g
    (the old ^ multiline anchor only matched the first tag for single-line PGN files).
  - tablebase.js _parsePGN + stats.html parsePGN: brace-comment stripping now replaces
    with a SPACE instead of empty string (prevents e4{...}e5 → e4e5 concatenation).
  - tablebase.js _parsePGN: variation comment isolation — [%eval]/[%csl]/[%cal] tags
    now only extracted at _depth===0 (main line). Previously, comments inside variations
    (...) were parsed and their position-specific tags contaminated the next main-line
    move's annotations. Free-text comments still extracted at all depths (with [var] prefix).
  - tablebase.js importPGN: now computes isCheck (via inCheck on post-move state) and
    isCastling (via _castleSide on pre-move state + parsed move) for each imported move.
    Previously these fields were missing → red check arrows + green escape arrows were
    never generated for imported PGNs.
  - game-logic.js _castleSide: now accepts optional `s` (state) parameter for the fallback
    castling detection — uses s.board / s.castlingRights instead of the global gameState.
    Fixes review/stats "extra kings" board corruption during PGN replay.
  - stats.html executeMove: castling detection now requires king on home row + correct
    distance + empty destination + castling right present (was: any king move to col 6/2).
    Also: castling rights now cleared on king/rook move + rook capture (was missing).
  - index.html.tpl: eval-chart palette unified to blue-vs-red in BOTH modes:
    Light mode:  --chart-line #4a4a52 → #2c5f8d (steel blue), --chart-fill #2c2c34 → #c0392b (deep red),
                 --chart-critical #5a5a66 → #d4a017 (gold)
    Dark mode:   --chart-line #E8E8F0 → #5dade2 (sky blue), --chart-fill #5dade2 → #e74c3c (warm red),
                 --chart-grid #333 → #4a3020 (dark warm brown), --chart-axis #666 → #8a6a3a (medium warm brown)
  - ui.js _buildEvalTrendSVG: data point outline now uses --chart-text-stroke variable
    (theme-aware) instead of hardcoded rgba values; fallback colors updated to dark-mode palette.
v1.0.8 Phase 51: game-logic.js _castleSide() fix — now checks mv.to.castle
  (set by pseudoMoves) in addition to mv.castle (set by executeMove). Fixes
  PGN round-trip castling failure (O-O/O-O-O only moved the king in replay).
  Also: i18n 'book' label changed {zh:'开局库',en:'Book'} → {zh:'平常',en:'Mediocre'}.
  Also: index.html.tpl --chart-fill dark-mode color #1A1A2E → #5dade2 (visibility).
v1.0.8 Phase 25: worker-pool.js was REIMPLEMENTED (robust Web Worker pool)
  and wired into stats.html (heatmap-stats offloading). The module order is
  now: game-logic → chess960 → pgn-standard → worker-pool → ai-bridge →
  tablebase → eco-data → ui (8 modules).
v1.0.8 Phase 24: worker-pool.js was previously DELETED (581 lines of dead
  code — the original v1.0.4 implementation was never called). Phase 25
  reimplemented it robustly and correctly wired it in.

License classification by file:
  - game-logic.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      PGN disambiguation and SAN notation logic from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder(): prepends a null placeholder to
          moveRecords when a new game starts with Black to move (FEN/setup
          /PGN import paths). Syncs stateHistory[0].moveRecords so the
          placeholder survives undo back to the opening.
        - boardVersion integer on game state (incremented by makeMv /
          makeMvInPlace / _refreshStateAfterSetup, restored by unmakeMv,
          initialized to 1 by fenToState / initState) — used by the
          _updateBoardIncremental dirty check for ~100x faster render ticks.
        - moveAlg() disambiguation: replaced cloneB-per-candidate with
          makeMvInPlace/unmakeMv — eliminates up to 8 board clones per
          moveAlg call (e.g. 8 pawns that could capture on the same file).
        - pieceZobristIdx(): hoisted the {pawn:0,knight:1,...} type-index
          lookup to module scope (_PIECE_TYPE_IDX) instead of building a
          fresh object literal on every call (32+ calls per computeHash).
        - isDeadPosition(): single-pass 64-square scan with early returns
          (pawns/rooks/queens → not dead) instead of allocating a pcs[]
          array + multiple .filter()/.map() passes. Bishop square-color
          parity tracked inline. Same FIDE 5.2.2 coverage, ~3x faster.
  - ai-bridge.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      Engine communication patterns from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _buildPGNString() now appends `{score eval_word}` after every
          move with a cached eval in _reviewEvalCache, and
          `{SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}` every 5 moves (engine name,
          depth, score, WDL). Helper: _formatPGNEvalAnnotation().
        - exportPGNToFile() + onPGNExported() for SAF-based PGN export.
        - _fileBrowserSelect() no longer calls showToast() after
          bridge.importSettings() — the onSettingsImported callback is
          the single source of truth for the import result toast,
          eliminating the duplicate-toast bug.
        - _safeExecute() wrapper in Java side catches
          RejectedExecutionException from engineExecutor and notifies
          JS via onEngineError (see StockfishNative.java).
        - restartCurrentEngine() and onEngineRestarting() both clear
          _reviewEvalCache, _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult,
          _lastEngineVariation to prevent stale evals from the old
          engine instance.
        - Ponder-Hit fix: uses JS-side cached _lastPonderMoveFromEngine
          instead of re-calling Java getLastPonderMove() (which is a
          one-shot read).
        - PV variation cache + fork grafting: _pvCache (Map) +
          _convertPVtoSANCached() + _checkPVDivergence(). Caches the
          converted SAN + post-state for every UCI prefix encountered
          during a single _processDeferredVariations() call, keyed by
          (state.hash, uciPrefix). MultiPV lines sharing a common prefix
          (e.g. e4 e5 Nf3) now convert the prefix exactly once instead
          of N times. Cache is cleared per-search (bounded at 200 entries).
        - generateFEN(): hoisted the PIECE_FEN lookup table to module
          scope (_PIECE_FEN) instead of allocating a fresh
          {white:{...},black:{...}} object on every call. generateFEN
          is called on every AI move, hint, and eval request.
        - _esc() / _escJs(): single-pass regex with callback + lookup
          map instead of 5 chained .replace() calls (5 intermediate
          string allocations → 1). These helpers are called on every
          move notation, file path, and ECO name during render.
        - _formatPGNEvalAnnotation(): explicit parenthesization of the
          mate-detection condition + Number() coercion of cached
          mate/eval values (defensive against JSON string values).
  - ui.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      UI layout and interaction patterns from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - startGame() now auto-fills ECO opening moves into moveRecords
          with proper SAN notation as it replays each move — the user
          sees the full opening sequence from move #1, no "..."
          placeholder needed.
        - _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder() called at 4 new-game entry
          points (startGame, _applyImportedFEN, exitSetup, importPGN).
        - redoMove() no longer calls doAIMove() — the redo stack
          contains pre-recorded moves; triggering a fresh AI search
          would corrupt the stack.
        - "Play Again" button now shows ⚔️ prefix.
        - executeMove() setTimeout(420ms) callback captures
          gameState.hash before the timeout and aborts if it changes,
          preventing stale callbacks from overwriting new state during
          undo/redo/flip (the "ghost game-over banner" bug).
        - doAIMove() moved out of the rAF callback into setTimeout(0)
          so the browser can paint the post-move UI before the engine
          starts thinking.
        - toggleSetup() simplified — removed dead 'play' status check.
        - infoCtrl now references the control-map entry directly
          instead of allocating a fresh {white,black} object per render.
        - _cachedBwrap liveness check changed from parentNode to
          document.body.contains() for stricter validation.
        - _updateSingleSq(): signature-based dirty check — builds a
          cheap signature string (piece + selection + last-move +
          check + legal + control-map + anim) and skips all DOM writes
          (style.background, className, innerHTML) when the signature
          hasn't changed. Previously rebuilt innerHTML for all 64
          squares on every engine-progress callback (~10-50/sec).
        - _getSqBg(): removed unused _sqBgCache declaration + dead
          lastFrom/lastTo computation (variables were computed but
          never used in the return value).
  - tablebase.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      PGN parsing logic (GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner) from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _applyImportedFEN() and importPGN() call
          _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder() when the imported position
          has Black to move.
        - PGN variation continuation loop changed from `break` (truncate
          entire variation on first unparseable token) to `continue`
          (skip only that token, keep parsing the rest). moveAlg-based
          forgiving fallback applied uniformly to every token.
        - When an unparseable token is skipped, the side-to-move and
          move number now advance — a skipped move still consumes a
          turn per PGN spec, otherwise the next token would be
          attributed to the wrong side, desynchronizing the variation.
        - _tbCache (tablebase LRU cache) now refreshes on hit (delete +
          set) so frequently-accessed entries don't get evicted before
          cold entries. Previously only `get` was called without
          reordering, defeating LRU semantics.
  - ai-bridge.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      v1.0.2 additional fixes (second-pass review):
        - _formatVariationGroups(): variation line numbers are now assigned
          SEQUENTIALLY (1, 2, 3, ...) based on array position, not derived
          from group/mpvIndex/lineNum fields. The old scheme could collide
          (mainline=1, mpvIndex=0 also=1) producing duplicate "🌿线1"
          labels when both were attached to the same move (common after
          Flip or when multiple MultiPV lines diverge at the same move).
        - _checkPVDivergenceSANs(): added same-SAN dedup guard to prevent
          the same variation from being attached multiple times.
        - _mrToUci(): knight promotion letter 'k' → 'n' (UCI spec). Was
          causing false PV divergence for every knight promotion.
        - _resetGameUIState() in ui.js now resets isAIThinking,
          _aiSafetyTimerId, _aiRetryCount, _evalLoading, _sfEvalReady,
          _ponderGen, _ponderMoveSAN, _ponderBarInfo, _pendingPonderMoveUCI,
          _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult, _lastEngineVariation — prevents
          stale AI state from leaking into a new game (was causing "AI
          never moves" if the user started a new game during AI thinking).
        - onBestMove(): removed the `moveRecords.length > 0` guard so
          variations are tracked even when the AI plays the first move
          (player plays Black). Was causing no 🌿 variation lines for
          the AI's first move when playing Black.
        - _aiRetryCount reset added to onEngineReady() and
          onEngineRestarting() — prevents the retry counter from
          carrying over after a crash-recovery, which could immediately
          hit the 3-retry cap and show "AI timeout" despite the engine
          just having recovered.
        - onStatsRequestReview(): shows a toast when moveRecords is empty
          instead of silently returning.
        - _reviewEvalCache gains a peek() method (read without LRU
          refresh); iteration loops in _buildEvalTrendSVG,
          _findCriticalMoves, move-list render, and openStatsPage use
          peek() to avoid churning the Map.
        - openStatsPage() now also sends moveRecords (from/to/piece/
          captured/promotion/notation) in the payload — the stats page
          uses them to replay moves correctly instead of re-parsing the
          PGN string with its simplified parser (which cascade-failed
          on complex moves, capping the total move count).
        - Removed dead _checkPVDivergence(pv1, pv2) function (shadowed
          by the no-arg _checkPVDivergence() that iterates
          _pendingEnginePVs — JS last-declaration-wins rule made the
          former unreachable).
        - Removed onStatsRequestImport() and its export (stats import
          now stays inside StatsActivity).
        - executeMove() ponder-hit check: promotion piece name → UCI
          letter (queen→'q' etc.) so promotion moves can match the
          engine's UCI ponder move (was always failing, defeating
          ponder for all promotions).
        - makeMv() in game-logic.js: reuse capPiece for Zobrist hash
          instead of re-reading from original state (redundant read).
        - v1.0.2 (qw3.7max audit) — 7 optimizations from the external
          code-review report, all implemented:
          (1) _updateBoardLightweight(): state-comparison logic (_selChanged,
              _newHover→_infoChanged) rewritten with optional chaining (?.)
              for cleaner null-safe comparison; renamed _newHover to
              _infoChanged (the variable tracks info-square changes, not
              just hover).
          (2) Review move-classification span: _mcls.color and _mcls.label
              now wrapped in _esc() for defensive XSS protection (currently
              redundant since _classifyMove returns internal constants, but
              guards against future changes).
          (3) scrollIntoView behavior:'instant' → 'auto' at 2 call sites
              (review-mode auto-scroll) for broader compatibility with
              older WebView engines that don't support the CSSOM View
              'instant' value.
          (4) Review auto-scroll: rAF+setTimeout(0) → double rAF. The first
              rAF fires after layout, the second after paint — reading
              layout info (scrollIntoView) in the second rAF guarantees no
              forced synchronous layout (layout thrashing). The old
              rAF+setTimeout(0) pattern couldn't guarantee layout was
              complete because setTimeout is a macrotask that may run
              before the browser's layout/paint step.
          (5) _sqElCache: 2D array-of-arrays → 1D array indexed by (r*8+c).
              Single contiguous allocation, no nested array objects, one
              fewer pointer dereference per access. With 10-50 engine
              progress callbacks/sec, this shaves a small but measurable
              amount off the hot incremental-update path.
          (6) _isMoverWhite: ((i+1)%2)===1 → (i%2)===0 (mathematically
              equivalent, eliminates the unnecessary +1). Applied at 2
              sites in ui.js (review move-list render + _findCriticalMoves).
          (7) _rListEl: module-level cache of the review-moves-list element,
              avoids getElementById('reviewMovesList') on every render's
              scroll-into-view path. Assigned after full render, cleared on
              cache invalidation.
          (8) Review move-classification span: string concatenation (+=)
              → ES6 template literal for readability (the span is built
              once per reviewed move, not in a hot loop).
  - eco-data.js: AGPL v3 (original)
      ECO opening data from lichess-org/chess-openings (CC0).
      Code is original — not derived from DroidFish.
  - index.html.tpl: GPL v3 (v1.0.8 PHASE 37 reclassification)
      v1.0.8 PHASE 37/49: reclassified AGPL v3 → GPL v3. The CSS layout
      patterns and theme-variable structure follow DroidFish-derived
      conventions; the template is bundled with the GPL v3 JS modules by
      build-chess.py, so GPL v3 applies to the combined work to avoid
      license fragmentation.
  - build-chess.py: AGPL v3 (original build script)
      (v1.0.2: deleted build-chess.sh — byte-for-byte duplicate of build-chess.py)

v1.0.2 stats.html updates (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived PGN parsing):
  - parsePGN() now checks for _payload.moveRecords (sent by the main
    app). If present, calls parseFromMoveRecords() to replay the
    authoritative move list via executeMove() — avoids the simplified
    SAN parser's cascade-failure bug that capped total moves at ~98.
  - parseFromMoveRecords(): converts algebraic strings ("e2") to
    {row, col} objects (the main app stores from/to as strings; stats
    executeMove expects objects). Skips null placeholders.
  - renderPGNText() / renderSAN(): piece symbols now wrapped in their
    own <span class="piece-white/piece-black"> with the same
    color/stroke/glow as the main board. CSS specificity increased
    (.pgn-display .move .piece-white) so the piece color overrides
    .pgn-display .move. Previously the piece symbols were
    cream-colored (same as the rest of the move text) because
    .pgn-display .move (specificity 0,2,0) overrode .piece-white
    (specificity 0,1,0).
  - PGN import (📂 Select PGN File) now opens SAF picker directly
    from StatsActivity via statsSelectPGNFile() bridge method.
    onStatsPGNFileRead(content) callback updates the payload in place.
  - _statsPastePGN() no longer checks AndroidBridge.statsRequestImport
    (removed orphaned feature check).

v1.0.4 EXPANSION (this round) — in stats.html and chess.src/*.js:
  - worker-pool.js (NEW FILE, AGPL v3): Web Worker pool implementation.
      Worker source inlined as a string and instantiated via Blob URL
      (compatible with WebView CSP). Worker ships with slim chess
      primitives (attacked, getCtrlMap, makeMvInPlace, fenToState,
      stateToFEN, parsePGN, computeHeatmapStats). Public Promise-based
      APIs: workerParsePGN(), workerComputeHeatmapStats(),
      workerGetCtrlMap(). Inline fallback when Workers unavailable.
  - pgn-standard.js (EXPANDED, AGPL v3): added formatEmtTag() for
      [%emt HH:MM:SS]; NAG_MAP, nagToSymbol(), symbolToNag(),
      formatNagToken() for $1-$19 NAGs; formatCslTag(), formatCalTag(),
      parseCslTag(), parseCalTag() for Lichess/Chessbase visual
      annotations; parseTimeControl(), formatTimeControl() supporting
      all 6 TimeControl formats (sudden/fischer/bronstein/usdelay/
      staged/hourglass).
  - ui.js (EXPANDED, AGPL v3 for original parts / GPL v3 for
      DroidFish-derived UI patterns): New Game dialog gains a "Time
      Control" section (5-mode dropdown + base/increment/delay inputs).
      New state vars: dlgTimeControl, gameClocks, gameClockTimerId,
      gameClockExpired. New functions: initGameClocks(),
      _tickGameClock(), _onGameClockExpired(), recordMoveEnd(),
      formatClock(), _updateClockDisplay(),
      _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations(),
      _getVisualAnnotations(). executeMove() now calls recordMoveEnd()
      and _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations() per move. Visual
      annotations cache (_visualAnnotationsCache) keyed by moveRecords
      index. Selection rules: Blue = top-3 own-piece→important-square
      control paths; Red = checker→checked king path; Green = checked
      king's adjacent safe squares; Yellow = mover→opponent's queen path.
  - ai-bridge.js (EXPANDED, GPL v3 — DroidFish-derived patterns):
      _buildPGNString() now emits [TimeControl "..."] header when game
      is timed; per-move comments now include [%emt] (untimed) or
      [%clk] (timed), plus [%csl] and [%cal] from the visual
      annotations cache.
  - tablebase.js (EXPANDED, GPL v3 — DroidFish-derived PGN parsing):
      fenToState() now detects Shredder-FEN castling rights (any letter
      A-H/a-h in castling field) and parses them via
      parseShredderCastling() from chess960.js. _parsePGN() extracts
      the [Variant "Chess960"] tag. importPGN() calls
      setChess960Mode(true) for Chess960 games and derives SP-ID.
  - game-logic.js (EXPANDED, GPL v3 — DroidFish-derived SAN logic):
      Added i18n strings for Chess960 UI (chess960_*) and time-control
      UI (time_control_*). loading_title updated to v1.0.4.
  - index.html.tpl (AGPL v3): <title>Regalia v1.0.4</title>.
  - chess960.js (NEW in prior v1.0.4 round, AGPL v3): SP-ID generator,
      Shredder-FEN castling rights, 960 castling rules.
  - stats.html (EXPANDED, GPL v3 — DroidFish-derived PGN parsing):
      New "Heatmap Control Statistics" section (per-square avg control
      across all positions, strongest/weakest square detection, center
      control trend) and new "Visual Annotations" section (tallies
      [%csl] G/B/R/Y counts and NAG $1-$6 distribution from PGN text).
      New i18n strings for both sections.

v1.0.4 changes (in stats.html and chess.src/*.js):
  - chess960.js (NEW FILE): Chess960 implementation.
  - pgn-standard.js (NEW FILE): standardized PGN encoder/decoder.
  - ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNString() rewritten to use composePGN() —
    emits Seven-Tag Roster + supplementary tags.
  - tablebase.js: fenToState() detects Shredder-FEN castling rights.
  - game-logic.js: Chess960 UI i18n strings; loading_title → v1.0.4.
  - ui.js: New Game dialog Chess960 toggle; _startGameImpl() branches
    on dlgChess960. Version badge → v1.0.4.
  - index.html.tpl: <title>Regalia v1.0.4</title>.
  - stats.html: Heatmap Control Statistics section.
  - All i18n strings bilingual (zh/en).

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev17-19 changes (in chess.src/*.js):
  - ai-bridge.js (Rev17): _reviewEvalCache dual-writes to localStorage
    and AndroidBridge.persistentSet (SharedPreferences). On construction,
    reads localStorage first, falls back to persistentGet, rehydrates
    localStorage. Removed 200-entry LRU cap in Rev18 (now unlimited).
    Added PGN cache manager state: showPGNCacheManager, _pgnCacheList,
    _pgnCacheSelected.
  - game-logic.js (Rev17): toggleLang() and startup auto-detect dual-write
    and fallback-read Regalia_lang. Rev18: added 18 new i18n keys for
    cache manager UI (pgn_cache_manager, pgn_cache_save_current, etc.).
    Rev19: added enter_review_hint key.
  - ui.js (Rev17): error boundary _tryRecovery IIFE dual-writes
    Regalia_recovery. Rev18: added 📚 button in review toolbar (between
    🌗/🌈 and 📝 FEN); added complete cache manager modal
    (openPGNCacheManager, _refreshPGNCacheList, _pgnCacheToggleSel,
    _pgnCacheSaveCurrent, _pgnCacheImport, _pgnCacheDeleteSelected,
    _renderPGNCacheManager, _escapeHTML, _jsAttrEncode). Rev19: fixed
    onclick syntax error (JSON.stringify in double-quoted attributes
    broke parsing — replaced with _jsAttrEncode that HTML-escapes the
    JSON string's double quotes as &quot;). Rev19: enterReview() no
    longer returns early on empty moveRecords — allows entering review
    with zero moves so user can use 📚/🗃️ to import. "暂无走法记录"
    text is now clickable to enter review mode.
  - tablebase.js (Rev17): _parsePGN header-strip regex synced to
    /^\[[^\]]*\]/gm (line-anchored).
  - worker-pool.js (Rev17): stringified parsePGN regex synced to
    /^\\[[^\\]]*\\]/gm (double-escaped for JS string template).

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev20 changes (in chess.src/*.js):
  - ai-bridge.js (Rev20): _reviewEvalCache rewritten to use dedicated
    eval_cache.json file (atomic write via saveEvalCacheSync Java
    interface). Reads from loadEvalCacheSync at construction (instant).
    Debounce reduced 500ms→150ms. Added _flushSync() method called by
    pagehide/visibilitychange/beforeunload + Java onPause/onStop/
    onUserLeaveHint (via window._flushReviewEvalCache). Removed unused
    _pgnCacheToast variable.
  - game-logic.js (Rev20): added 8 new i18n keys for rename/tags
    features (pgn_cache_rename, pgn_cache_rename_prompt,
    pgn_cache_renamed, pgn_cache_rename_failed, pgn_cache_tags,
    pgn_cache_tags_prompt, pgn_cache_tags_saved,
    pgn_cache_tags_save_failed) — all zh/en.
  - ui.js (Rev20): review toolbar button order adjusted — 🌗/🌈 moved
    to right of 💬Vars toggle, left of 📝 PGN. _renderPGNCacheManager
    updated: each entry now has three vertical icon buttons (✏️ Rename,
    🔖 Tags, 📥 Import); tags displayed as gold capsule chips below
    entry name. New functions: _pgnCacheRename(oldName),
    _pgnCacheEditTags(name).

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev21 changes (in chess.src/*.js):
  - ai-bridge.js (Rev21): _reviewEvalCache.set()/.delete()/.clear() now
    trigger SYNCHRONOUS write IMMEDIATELY (no debounce). The 150ms
    debounce path is retained as fallback but currently unused (all
    callers use forceSync=true). New state vars: _pgnCacheFilter,
    _pgnCacheFilterInput.
  - game-logic.js (Rev21): added 7 new i18n keys for filter/search
    features (pgn_cache_search_placeholder, pgn_cache_search_apply,
    pgn_cache_search_clear, pgn_cache_filter_all, pgn_cache_filter_by_tag,
    pgn_cache_filter_status, pgn_cache_filter_no_match) — all zh/en.
  - ui.js (Rev21): _renderPGNCacheManager completely reworked to add
    search/filter UI at the top: text search box + 🔍 apply button +
    ✕ clear button + tag-chip quick-filter row + filter status bar.
    Tag chips below entry names are now clickable (trigger
    _pgnCacheFilterByTag). _pgnCacheSelectAll now only selects visible
    (filtered) entries. Count display shows "visible/total" when filtered.
    Empty-result hint shown when filter has no matches. Filter state
    auto-cleared on close/reopen. New functions: _pgnCacheOnSearchInput(v),
    _pgnCacheApplyFilter(), _pgnCacheClearFilter(), _pgnCacheFilterByTag(tag),
    _pgnCacheEntryMatchesFilter(entry,filter), _pgnCacheCollectAllTags().
    openPGNCacheManager() and _pgnCacheClose() now reset filter state.

v1.0.3 changes (in stats.html and chess.src/*.js):
  - ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNComment() format uses a single space as
    separator between thinking time and eval annotation.
    Examples: "{3.2s +0.5 略优}", "{3.2s SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}",
    "{3.2s}", "{+0.5 略优}" (eval only — no separator). Backward
    compatible with the earlier em-dash format on the parsing side.
  - game-logic.js: loading_title and built_in_only strings updated
    from v1.0.2 → v1.0.3.
  - ui.js: version badge (<span class="ver">v1.0.3</span>), about
    dialog (v1.0.3), and render-error fallback page (v1.0.3) updated.
  - index.html.tpl: <title>Regalia v1.0.3</title>.
  - stats.html (NOT in chess.src/, lives in assets/ directly):
      * stateToFEN(state): NEW — generates a FEN string from a game
        state (board placement, side to move, castling, en passant,
        halfmove clock, fullmove number).
      * extractMoveTimes(pgnText): NEW — extracts per-move thinking
        times from PGN comments in the {<sec>s ...} (v1.0.3),
        {<sec>s——...} (earlier em-dash format, back-compat), and [%clk HH:MM:SS]
        formats. Returns {usedTimes, clkTimes} arrays indexed by
        mainline move index.
      * formatTime(sec): NEW — human-readable time formatting
        (e.g. "12.3s", "3m 25s", "1h 12m 30s").
      * renderTimeChart(times): NEW — SVG bar chart of per-move
        thinking time. White moves = white bars, Black = blue bars.
      * renderFENPanel(effectiveParsed, selectedIdx): NEW — FEN
        display panel below the PGN text panel. Shows the FEN of the
        position after the selected move (mainline or variation),
        auto-generated from the post-state. Includes a copy-to-clipboard
        button (uses navigator.clipboard with execCommand fallback).
      * selectVariationMove(varId, varClickedIdx): NEW — handles
        variation-move clicks. Builds a synthetic move sequence:
        mainline[0..mainIdxBefore-1] + variation moves[0..varClickedIdx],
        where mainIdxBefore is the index of the mainline move that the
        variation's first move REPLACES. The synthetic sequence is used
        for ALL stats computation, giving per-position statistics for
        variation lines.
      * _variations[] array: NEW — registered by renderPGNText() as it
        walks the PGN. Each entry has {mainIdxBefore, moves:[SAN],
        sideAtStart}. Used by selectVariationMove() to reconstruct the
        synthetic sequence.
      * _variationMoves / _variationMeta: NEW state variables holding
        the current variation selection (mutually exclusive with
        _selectedMoveIdx for mainline selection).
      * renderStats() Time Management section: REPLACED the v1.0.2
        placeholder (which only counted [%clk] comments) with a
        comprehensive analysis: total/White/Black time, avg per move,
        slowest/fastest move, volatility (stddev), long-think count,
        quick-move count, phase distribution (opening/midgame/endgame),
        per-move time bar chart.
      * render() function: now resets _variations before each render,
        computes effectiveParsed (mainline slice, variation synthetic,
        or full), adds a selection banner above the PGN text panel,
        and inserts the FEN panel between PGN text and stats.
      * Bilingual UI strings: 30+ new i18n keys added (fen_label,
        fen_hint, fen_copy, time_*, variation_marker, select_hint,
        select_var_hint, etc.) for the existing ↔️ Chinese/English
        language toggle.
      * CSS: new .fen-panel, .time-chart-bar styles; responsive
        @media tweaks for small screens.

v1.0.3 patch changes (in addition to the v1.0.3 baseline above):
  - tablebase.js (GPL v3):
      * importPGN() variation post-process: Type A vs Type B distinction.
        The relocate loop now skips Type A variations (alternatives to the
        owning move — firstMoveIsWhite matches (mi%2===0)) so they remain
        attached to the owning move with correct move numbers. Previously
        Type A variations were incorrectly relocated to mi+1 and mislabeled
        as Type B continuations, producing nonsensical displays like
        "7... hxg3 Qxh1 8.Nc3 ..." for a variation that should be
        "7. hxg3 Qxh1 8.Nc3 ..." (White's alternative to 7.Kf2). This
        was the root cause of app-exported PGNs with variations failing
        to round-trip on re-import.
      * importPGN() and _applyImportedFEN(): set the new global
        _importedStartMoveNum from the FEN's fullMoveNumber so the move
        list, review mode, and PGN export display correct move numbers
        (e.g. "4. Bxf7+ Kxf7 5. Ne5" for a FEN starting at move 4,
        instead of "1. Bxf7+ Kxf7 2. Ne5").
      * _parsePGN() Phase 4 (cascade-failure fix): when a main-line token
        fails to parse, push a "skipped" placeholder entry (with
        skipped:true + skippedSAN) so moveRecords indices stay aligned
        with PGN move numbers, AND advance the side-to-move (bump
        fullMoveNumber if black was to move) so subsequent tokens have a
        chance to parse. Previously, a single invalid token would leave
        the side-to-move unchanged, causing EVERY subsequent token to
        also fail (wrong side's move) — manifesting as "only the first N
        moves import, the rest are silently dropped". Safety cap: 5
        consecutive skips stops the parse. Symptom was: app-exported
        PGNs with one illegal move imported only the prefix up to that
        move; now all OTHER moves import with a single "—" marker where
        the illegal move was.
      * importPGN() replay loop: handle "skipped" placeholder moves by
        pushing a null moveRecord (same as the black-to-move placeholder)
        so the display layer renders a dimmed "..." marker, keeping
        moveRecords indices aligned with PGN move numbers.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3):
      * _buildPGNString(): uses _importedStartMoveNum as the move-pair
        number offset so PGN exports from a FEN-started game preserve the
        original move numbers from the FEN header.
      * New global _importedStartMoveNum (default 1) tracks the starting
        move number for PGN/FEN imports. Reset to 1 by startGame() and
        exitSetup() in ui.js.
  - ui.js (GPL v3):
      * Move history list (main mode + review mode): move-pair numbers
        now use _importedStartMoveNum as the offset. Click-to-review
        onclick handlers now use the moveRecords index `i` (stored in
        pair.wi / pair.bi) instead of computing reviewStep from pr.n,
        so the reviewStep is correct regardless of the FEN offset.
      * _exitSetupImpl() and _startGameImpl(): reset/set
        _importedStartMoveNum to track the starting move number for
        setup-mode positions and to reset to 1 for fresh games.
      * Landscape review mode: COMPLETE REDESIGN. The old layout put
        board + chart + controls all in .review-left (left column) with
        the move list in .review-moves (right column). The new layout
        splits into .review-top (board + moves, side by side) and
        .review-bottom (chart + slider + eval + nav + analyze, full
        width edge-to-edge). The whole .review-body scrolls vertically
        when content overflows. Key changes:
        - Chart now spans FULL viewport width (edge-to-edge, no gaps)
          instead of being squeezed under the board.
        - Chart height is ~35% of viewport height (generous).
        - Move list width is capped at 90% of board width (always
          narrower than the board, per user requirement).
        - Nav buttons (⏮ ◀ ▶ ⏭) are wrapped in .review-nav with
          flex:1 1 0 on each button so they stretch horizontally to
          fill the full width.
        - Board sizing: 60% of viewport height for the board+moves row,
          65% of viewport width for the board (leaving 35% for moves).
      * Portrait review mode: unchanged (original stacked layout).
      * v1.0.3-p3 hotfix: fixed a syntax error introduced by v1.0.3-p2's
        landscape review refactor — the if/else split for landscape/portrait
        move-list rendering forgot the closing `}` for the `if(reviewMode){`
        block, breaking the renderInternal() try/catch structure and causing
        a SyntaxError that made the entire chess.html script fail to parse
        (app showed a black screen on startup). Added the missing
        `} // close if(reviewMode)` after the move-list rendering branches.
      * v1.0.3-p4: landscape review layout — board+moves now FILL the full
        viewport width edge-to-edge. Removed the max-width cap on .review-moves
        (was calc(var(--rv-board-w) * 0.90)); move list now takes ALL remaining
        width via flex:1 1 0. .review-left padding changed from 2px 4px to 0
        so the board is flush with the screen's left edge. .review-moves
        padding tightened to 2px 2px 2px 4px so it's flush with the right
        edge. Board + moves together span 100% of viewport width with no
        gap between them. Board width cap changed from 65% to 55% of viewport
        width (move list gets ~45%). Move list scrolls vertically when
        content overflows (overflow-y:auto on .review-moves).
      * v1.0.3-p4: main-UI move-list scroll-position preservation. Before
        app.innerHTML=h, capture .mlist.scrollTop; after innerHTML replacement,
        restore it. This fixes the "move list keeps scrolling back to the top"
        bug caused by engine search triggering render() 10-50x/sec, each time
        rebuilding the DOM and resetting scrollTop to 0. Only runs in non-review
        mode (review mode has its own scrollIntoView logic).
      * v1.0.3-p5: landscape review layout — move list now has its OWN
        INDEPENDENT scroll viewport. .review-body changed from overflow-y:auto
        (whole-body scroll) to overflow:hidden (no body scroll). .review-top
        changed from flex:0 0 auto to flex:1 1 0 (fills all height above
        .review-bottom). .review-moves gets height:100% + min-height:0 so it
        fills the row height and scrolls internally via overflow-y:auto.
        .review-left gets height:100% + justify-content:center so the board is
        vertically centered in the row. The board stays fixed while only the
        move list scrolls. .review-bottom stays pinned at the bottom
        (flex:0 0 auto, no scroll).
      * v1.0.3-p5 audit fixes (first-principles code audit):
        - tablebase.js: removed a buggy regex that added an extra dot to move
          numbers (turned "1. e4" into "1.. e4"). The first regex already
          handles "1.e4" → "1. e4" and the third handles "1 e4" → "1. e4".
        - tablebase.js: removed dead `isCapture` computation in
          _executeAndRecord (was never read; move.enPassant is always undefined).
        - game-logic.js: queryECOBookMove now falls through to the level-1
          hash index when level-3 and level-2 both miss. Previously it degraded
          to a full ECO_OPENINGS scan, hurting ECO lookup performance for
          3+ move openings not in the level-3 index.
      * v1.0.3-p6: review move-list independent scroll — the REAL root cause
        was that scrollIntoView was called on EVERY render (10-50x/sec during
        engine analysis), yanking the move list back to the active move and
        preventing the user from scrolling independently. Now scrollIntoView
        only fires when reviewStep CHANGES (tracked via _lastReviewStepScrolled).
        Also removed the redundant setTimeout(50) scrollIntoView in reviewGoTo
        (renderInternal now handles it via the guard). enterReview resets
        _lastReviewStepScrolled to -2 so the first render after entering review
        mode scrolls the active move into view.
      * v1.0.3-p7: landscape review — TWO-LAYER SCROLL design. The body
        (.review-body) now scrolls vertically (overflow-y:auto, was overflow:
        hidden) so the user can scroll to see the chart, slider, eval bar, nav
        buttons, and analyze button when they don't all fit. The move list
        (.review-moves) keeps its OWN independent scroll viewport
        (overflow-y:auto with height = board height via --rv-board-h CSS var).
        Board sizing: board takes 60% of viewport width (ALWAYS > move-list
        width which gets 40%), NOT capped by REVIEW_CELL or viewport height.
        If the board is taller than the viewport, the user scrolls the body to
        see the board's bottom + chart + controls. Board + moves together fill
        100% of viewport width edge-to-edge, no gap. JS sets --rv-board-h CSS
        variable on .review-body so the move list height matches the board.
      * v1.0.3-p8: touch-slide on the review board now scrolls the whole
        review body. Two changes: (1) the global touchmove handler that
        preventDefault's board touches now SKIPS the preventDefault when
        reviewMode is true (so the browser's native scroll takes over);
        (2) the review board's .bgrid gets touch-action:pan-y (overriding the
        base .bgrid's touch-action:none) so vertical pans are handled by the
        browser as scroll. Horizontal pans are still blocked. Main-game mode
        is unaffected — board slides still don't scroll the page there.
      * v1.0.3-p9: review-body scroll preservation — capture
        .review-body.scrollTop before app.innerHTML=h and restore after,
        parallel to the v1.0.3-p4 .mlist preservation. Prevents the review
        body from yanking back to top on every render in landscape review mode.
      * v1.0.3-p9: move-list scroll isolation — replaced
        scrollIntoView({block:'center'}) (which scrolled ALL ancestors
        including .review-body) with a manual scrollTop computation on the
        move-list container only: _rList.scrollTop = _rAct.offsetTop -
        (_rList.clientHeight/2) + (_rAct.offsetHeight/2). This preserves the
        user's .review-body scroll position.
      * v1.0.3-p9 audit fixes: onBestMove staleness check moved before safety
        timer clear (ai-bridge.js — prevents doAIMove hang on stale bestmove);
        brace-comment loop iteration cap (tablebase.js — prevents infinite loop
        on unmatched `{`); stale comment cleanup (ui.js, index.html.tpl).
      * v1.0.3-p10: review nav buttons stretch full width in ALL orientations —
        promoted .review-nav and .review-nav .btn CSS from the landscape media
        query to base CSS (outside media queries). Nav buttons now fill the
        full row width in both portrait and landscape.
      * v1.0.3-p10: move-list scroll-to-active logic unified for both
        orientations — replaced single offsetTop read with a DOM walk that
        accumulates offsetTop from the active element up to the scroll
        container. Works correctly regardless of which element is the
        offsetParent (which differs between portrait and landscape layouts).
      * v1.0.3-p12: portrait chart width cap removed — was capped at
        min(viewportW-48, 400)-12 (max ~352px); now uses viewportW-12 for
        both orientations (unified with landscape).
      * v1.0.3-p11: eval trend chart SVG left/right padding reduced from
        36px to 8px — chart points and lines fully utilize horizontal space.
      * v1.0.3-p11: portrait move-list scroll root cause fix — the p10
        offsetParent walk failed in portrait because .review-moves has
        position:static, so .rmv-block's offsetParent jumped to
        .review-overlay (position:fixed), skipping the container. Replaced
        with getBoundingClientRect(): _offsetTop = _rActRect.top -
        _rListRect.top + _rList.scrollTop. Works in both orientations.
  - index.html.tpl (AGPL v3):
      * Landscape review CSS: complete redesign (see ui.js changes above).
        New classes: .review-top, .review-bottom, .review-nav.
        v1.0.3-p7: .review-body is overflow-y:auto (TWO-LAYER SCROLL — body
        scrolls to reveal chart/buttons). .review-top is flex:0 0 auto (height
        = board height, intrinsic). .review-moves has height:var(--rv-board-h)
        + min-height:0 + overflow-y:auto (INDEPENDENT scroll viewport matching
        board height). .review-bottom is flex:0 0 auto (pinned, visible via
        body scroll).
      * Removed the old per-size review overrides in compact/standard/
        tablet/large-tablet media queries (the new layout works at any
        size without per-size tweaks; only font sizes need adjustment
        on tall tablets, which remains).

The combined output (chess.html) is a combined work. The GPL v3 JavaScript
modules and AGPL v3 template retain their respective licenses. Since AGPL v3
imposes stricter requirements, its obligations effectively cover the entire
combined output.

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev22 changes:
    - ui.js: New Game dialog — Chess960 toggle moved directly below "Play Color"
      section (was below AI Book Moves). Removed the residual "Classic Openings
      (Optional)" title (<h3>T('classic_openings')</h3>) from the Chess960-OFF
      branch. Changed the Chess960-ON dedicated settings area heading from
      T('classic_openings') to T('chess960_label').
    - ui.js: PGN Cache Manager — removed the redundant 🔍 apply button (the
      search input now has enterkeyhint="search" so the soft keyboard's Enter
      key triggers search directly). Changed the input type from "text" to
      "search". Changed the ✏️/🔖/📥 button container from flex-direction:column
      to flex-direction:row (horizontal layout, same row).
    - ai-bridge.js: No changes (the eval-cache _flushSync() and critical-event
      handlers are already in place from Rev20/21).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev23 changes:
    - ai-bridge.js: onEngineRestarting() and restartCurrentEngine() no longer
      call _reviewEvalCache.clear() (which destroyed the ENTIRE persisted cache
      including other games' evals). Now only resets _reviewEvalRequestedStep=-1.
      Stockfish is deterministic, so other games' evals remain valid.
    - ai-bridge.js: _reviewEvalCache set()/delete() now use 150ms debounced
      write (was synchronous on every call since Rev21). _flushSync() from
      lifecycle handlers still forces immediate write. Performance: batch
      analyze-all of a 60-move game drops from 60x12MB writes to ~1.
    - ai-bridge.js: requestEngineEval() — removed redundant second cache check
      after _resetEvalState() (dead code — first check already returns on hit).
    - ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNString() — removed dead variable `moveNum` (was
      computed but never read; actual move number is `_moveNum`). Simplified
      _isBlackStart ternary (both branches identical) to direct formula.
    - ui.js: _pgnCacheOnSearchInput() — fixed stale comment referencing the
      removed 🔍 button (Rev22 removed it).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev24 changes:
    - ai-bridge.js: requestEngineEval() — when _reviewAnalyzeAllActive is
      true and cache hits, now calls _reviewAnalyzeAdvance() instead of
      returning silently (root cause #4 of analyze-all interruption).
    - ai-bridge.js: onEngineReady() — resumes analyze-all batch if
      _reviewAnalyzeAllActive is still true after engine auto-recovery
      (root cause #3 of analyze-all interruption).
    - ai-bridge.js: onEngineError() — no longer clears
      _reviewAnalyzeAllActive; resets the per-step safety timer to give
      the engine time to recover (root cause #5 of analyze-all interruption).
    - ai-bridge.js: requestEngineEval() — on synchronous engineEvalDeep()
      failure during batch, advances to the next step instead of stalling.
    - ai-bridge.js: NEW globals _humanPlayerName, playerWhite, playerBlack.
      _humanPlayerName is loaded synchronously from persistent storage at
      module init. _buildPGNString() uses _humanPlayerName for the human
      player's [White]/[Black] tag (falls back to T('you') when null).
    - ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNString(forceIncludeVariations) — new parameter
      bypasses the showVariations UI toggle so saved PGN archives always
      include variations.
    - game-logic.js: NEW i18n keys rename_player_hint, rename_player_prompt,
      rename_player_saved, rename_player_reset (zh/en).
    - tablebase.js: _parsePGN() — extracts [%eval ...] tags from {} comments
      BEFORE stripping them, returns extractedEvals array. importPGN()
      populates _reviewEvalCache from extracted evals (selectively clearing
      only the current game's entries first, preserving other games' caches).
      Also extracts playerWhite/playerBlack from PGN headers and populates
      _humanPlayerName if the human player's slot has a non-default name.
    - ui.js: reviewAnalyzeAll() rewritten — detects all-cached case and
      completes INSTANTLY (root cause #1 of analyze-all interruption).
      Per-step safety timer (60s) that RESETS on every advance (root cause
      #2 — old 5min global cap fired mid-analysis for long games). Stuck
      step is SKIPPED, not aborting the whole batch.
    - ui.js: _reviewAnalyzeResetSafetyTimer() — new helper that resets the
      per-step safety timer.
    - ui.js: Player bar — name now uses _humanPlayerName (rename feature).
      Clicking the name opens _renameHumanPlayer() prompt.
    - ui.js: _renameHumanPlayer() — new function. Prompts for a new name,
      persists via AndroidBridge.persistentSet('Regalia_humanName', ...).
      Empty/default input resets to T('you').
    - ui.js: _pgnCacheSaveCurrent() — ALWAYS uses _buildPGNString(true)
      (forceIncludeVariations=true) so saved PGN archives include the
      complete game record (variations + comments + [%eval] tags).
    - ui.js: Removed redundant 📥 Import button from PGN Cache Manager
      (clicking the entry name already imports it).
    - ui.js: _startGameImpl() — clears playerWhite/playerBlack on new game
      (preserves _humanPlayerName which is a persistent user preference).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev25 changes:
    - ui.js: New Game dialog — removed the redundant <h3>${T('chess960_label')}
      heading above the Chess960 dedicated settings section. The Chess960
      toggle above (with its own label) already makes the mode clear. The
      settings (SP-ID input, back-rank preview, note) now appear directly
      under the toggle. Removed in both Chinese and English modes.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev26 changes:
    - No changes to chess.src/ files. The Rev26 fix is entirely in
      stats.html (SAN regex alternative for non-capture pawn promotions).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev27 changes:
    - ui.js: New global document-level click handler intercepts all
      <a href="http(s)://..."> clicks anywhere in the document and routes
      them to AndroidBridge.openUrlInBrowser(). The default WebView
      navigation is suppressed via preventDefault(). In-page anchors and
      non-http(s) schemes are left alone.
    - ui.js: About dialog — the "Source code: ..." line is now a real
      <a> hyperlink (was plain text). All license links (AGPL, GPL) now
      also have rel="noopener" for defense-in-depth.
    - ui.js: Player bar — new 🏳️ Resign button next to the "Your turn"
      indicator (only visible during the human's turn, not in setup mode
      or after gameOver). Opens showResignConfirm dialog.
    - ui.js: New _resignGame() function — sets _resignWinnerColor (the
      AI's color), stops the engine (stop command + isAIThinking=false),
      stops the game clock, sets gameOver + _gameOverStatusKey='resign',
      plays a "lose" sound + ERROR haptic, markDirty(DIRTY_FULL).
    - ui.js: New showResignConfirm dialog with Yes/Cancel buttons. Yes
      calls _resignGame(); Cancel just closes the dialog. Back button
      (handleBackPress) also closes the dialog.
    - ui.js: _gameOverStrFromStatus('resign') now returns the resigner
      color (from _resignWinnerColor) + "认输"/"resigns".
    - ui.js: formatEval() resign case now uses _resignWinnerColor directly
      (was incorrectly trying to detect "White wins" in the resign text,
      which only contains "resigns").
    - ui.js: _resetGameUIState() resets showResignConfirm=false and
      _resignWinnerColor=null to prevent the previous game's resign state
      from leaking into the new game.
    - ai-bridge.js: New state variables showResignConfirm (bool) and
      _resignWinnerColor (string|null, 'white' or 'black' = the WINNER).
    - ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNString() — when _gameOverStatusKey==='resign',
      [Result] is set from _resignWinnerColor (1-0 if White wins, 0-1 if
      Black wins), checked FIRST so the resign text doesn't fall through
      to the default 1/2-1/2 draw branch. [Termination "Resignation"]
      supplementary tag added. Last move's comment appends
      "White resigns." / "Black resigns." per the 元宝 PGN report.
    - game-logic.js: New i18n keys — about_source_code_prefix,
      about_source_code_url (split from about_source_code so the URL can
      be a real link), resign_btn, resign_confirm_title, resign_confirm_msg,
      resign_yes, resign_no, white_resigns, black_resigns, resigns_suffix
      (zh/en).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev28 changes:
    - ai-bridge.js: openStatsPage() rewritten to ALWAYS rebuild the PGN
      from the current moveRecords via _buildPGNString(true)
      (forceIncludeVariations=true). Previously used _cachedOriginalPGN
      which became STALE when the user played new moves after importing.
      Now the stats page always reflects the current main/review game
      state. Falls back to _cachedOriginalPGN only if _buildPGNString
      returns empty (e.g., FEN-only imports with no moveRecords).
    - ui.js: New _showStatsImportBackPrompt(pgnText) function — called
      from MainActivity.onResume() via evaluateJavascript when
      StatsActivity.importedPGNOnStats is non-null. Uses the existing
      _withPGNSaveCheck mechanism to show the "💾 Save PGN file?" prompt
      before importing (if the current game has move records). The
      pending action is importPGN(pgn). New state variable
      _pendingStatsImportPGN stashes the PGN text for the import action
      closure.
    - ui.js: Game-over overlay emoji fix — the emoji was hardcoded to
      show 🤝 for all non-checkmate terminations. Now shows 🏳️ when
      _gameOverStatusKey==='resign' (matching the resign button's icon),
      and 🤝 only for genuine draws (stalemate, 50-move, repetition,
      insufficient material, agreement).
    - tablebase.js: _parsePGN() — the moveRecords.push({...}) in the PGN
      import path was missing the promotion field, so openStatsPage()
      serialized move records without promotion info, and the stats
      page's executeMove() couldn't apply the promotion (showed a pawn
      on the back rank instead of the promoted piece). Fixed by adding
      `promotion: move.promotion||null` to the pushed move record.
    - game-logic.js: New i18n keys — stats_import_back_title,
      stats_import_back_msg, stats_import_back_yes, stats_import_back_no,
      stats_import_back_cancel, stats_import_back_no_pgn (zh/en).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev29 changes:
    - tablebase.js (GPL v3): CRITICAL FIX — _parsePGN()→importPGN()'s
      moveRecords.push({...}) had `promotion: move.promotion||null` but
      the loop variable is `parsedMove`, not `move`. The ReferenceError
      was caught by the surrounding try/catch and shown as "Invalid PGN
      format" — EVERY PGN import failed. Fixed to
      `(parsedMove&&parsedMove.move&&parsedMove.move.promotion)||null`.
      Also: unclosed `{...}` comments now consume the rest of the
      movetext (PGN spec tolerant behavior) instead of generating bogus
      NULL placeholder tokens.
    - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): NAG classification fix — `if(delta>=90000)
      return 3; if(delta<=-90000) return 4;` used raw White-POV delta;
      Black's mating move was misclassified as $4 (blunder). Fixed to
      use side-relative moverDelta for ALL comparisons. Also: variation
      prefix `v.prefixEllipsisNum||vmn` falsy-0 bug fixed to explicit
      null check.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev30 changes:
    - ui.js (GPL v3): ROBUSTNESS — scroll position restoration fix.
      Added `_scrollRestoreGuard` flag that suppresses _onMlistScroll
      during programmatic scrollTop restore (was being corrupted by
      intermediate 'scroll' events from scroll-behavior:smooth
      animation). Save phase now reads scrollTop DIRECTLY from the
      live DOM. scroll-behavior temporarily switched to 'auto' during
      restore for instant positioning. Same pattern applied to
      .review-body in review mode. _scrollRestoreGuard reset on new
      game.
    - chess960.js (GPL v3): ROBUSTNESS — randomSPID() modulo bias
      elimination. Was `buf[0]%960` (slight bias: values 0..255 ~0.03%
      more likely than 256..959). Now uses rejection sampling: only
      accept values < 65280 (largest multiple of 960 ≤ 65536) before
      applying %960. Bounded retry count (8) prevents infinite loops.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev31 changes:
    - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): UCI COMPLIANCE — startPonder() now passes
      current gameClocks values (wtime/btime/winc/binc) to Java's
      startPonder(fen, wtime, btime, winc, binc) so the engine's `go
      ponder` includes time params. When ponderhit fires, the engine
      can switch to normal timed search. For untimed games, all zeros
      are passed. Dead code cleanup: removed unused `_unclosed` flag in
      tablebase.js _parsePGN.
    - tablebase.js (GPL v3): Dead code cleanup — removed unused
      `_unclosed` flag (was set but never read).
    - pgn-standard.js (GPL v3): Dead code cleanup — removed dead
      `ch==='\s'` comparison (single char never equals 2-char string);
      fixed composePGN() to avoid leading blank lines when tagPairs
      is empty.
    - game-logic.js (GPL v3): Review mode orientation-change scroll
      fix. Added _skipReviewBodyScrollRestore flag and orientationchange
      listener. On orientation change: force _lastReviewStepScrolled=-2
      (re-center active move in new layout), invalidate
      _mlistScrollState.valid (re-snapshot main move list).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev32 changes:
    - game-logic.js (GPL v3): CRITICAL FIX — ECO book move causing engine
      unresponsive. _requestStockfishMove() now resets _aiRetryCount=0
      when the ECO book provides a move (the engine wasn't called, so
      onBestMove never fired to reset the counter). Same fix applied to
      the tablebase-served move path. Without this, 3 consecutive book
      moves would trigger doAIMove()'s false "AI move failed after 3
      consecutive timeouts" branch, leaving the engine unresponsive.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.

