  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev54 changes (this round, per user spec):
    - ui.js (GPL v3): SIX improvements per user spec items 1-4 + audit:
      (1) Yellow arrow extension — when the mover's just-moved piece is a
          queen and its destination square is attacked by an opp piece
          ("主动把皇后移动到受威胁格"), that yellow arrow's priority is
          BOOSTED so it survives the cap-6 dedup. New _isQueenMovedIntoThreat
          flag computed from moveRecords[moveIdx].to + postState.board.
      (2) Blue arrow extension — when the mover's moved piece is itself at
          a square attacked by an opp piece ("主动把任意棋子移到受威胁格"),
          and this causes an opp piece to have 2+ threats on mover pieces,
          those opp multi-threat blue arrows are BOOSTED so they survive
          the cap-3 dedup. New _movedPieceThreatened flag.
      (3) Per-color arrow offsets — each color has a FIXED diagonal offset
          applied to BOTH start and end (so arrow direction is preserved):
            Blue  (B) → Upper-Left  (−X, −Y)
            Yellow(Y) → Lower-Left  (−X, +Y)
            Red   (R) → Upper-Right (+X, −Y)
            Green (G) → Lower-Right (+X, +Y)
          Magnitude ~12% of cell size. Makes overlapping arrows of different
          colors visually separable. New _colorOffsetMag + _colorOffset map
          in the SVG arrow rendering block.
      (4) Yellow square style — instead of CSS box-shadow inset (same as
          B/R/G), yellow squares now render as a SEPARATE overlay div inside
          the cell: rounded rectangle (border-radius ~15% of cell), 2px
          solid yellow border, positioned with ~10% inset on all sides so
          the four corners leave gaps where other colors' box-shadow insets
          remain visible underneath. Z-index 5 (above cell, below SVG
          arrows at z-index 10). New _isYellowSquare flag + overlay div
          emission in the cell render loop.
      (5) (Roll-only rotation is implemented in StabilizationHelper.java,
          not in chess.src/ — see java/com/Regalia/README.license.)
      (6) (First-principles anti-shake audit is implemented in
          StabilizationHelper.java — see java/com/Regalia/README.license.)
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to ai-bridge.js, chess960.js, eco-data.js, game-logic.js,
      worker-pool.js, pgn-standard.js, tablebase.js, index.html.tpl.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev55 changes (line-by-line code audit):
    - game-logic.js (GPL v3): PERF optimization in getCtrlMap — hoisted the
      attacker-position object out of the inner loop. Each piece at (r,c)
      attacks multiple squares, but its `position` field is the SAME for all
      those pushes. Previously allocated a fresh {row:r,col:c} object on every
      push (~256 allocations per ctrl-map = per render tick when heatmap is on).
      Now allocates ONE position object per piece (max 32) and reuses it.
      Consumers (ui.js visual annotation code, worker-pool) only READ the
      position field, so sharing is safe.
    - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): consistency fix — the worker's fenToState()
      checked `parts.length<4`, while the main-thread fenToState in
      tablebase.js checks `parts.length<2`. A minimal FEN with just board +
      side-to-move (e.g. for setup-mode preview) was accepted by main but
      rejected by worker. Changed worker to `<2` for consistency.
    - chess960.js (AGPL v3): cleaned up misleading stale comment in
      parseShredderCastling() — the comment claimed the prior line was "dead
      code" but that was already consolidated in v1.0.4 into a single `else
      if`. The code was correct; only the comment was stale.
    - No changes to ai-bridge.js, tablebase.js, pgn-standard.js, eco-data.js,
      ui.js, index.html.tpl.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev56 changes (MultiPV + dirty-flag pipeline audit):
    - ai-bridge.js (AGPL v3): FOUR improvements to the MultiPV processing path:
      (1) PERF: _updateMultiPVDisplay() — added a per-line signature cache
          (_multiPVDisplayCache) so we skip the expensive _convertPVtoSAN()
          call when a PV line's content hasn't changed since the last display
          update. Previously, _updateMultiPVDisplay was called on every
          onMultiPVProgress AND on every onEngineProgress (when
          _cachedMultiPV>1), re-converting ALL PV lines from UCI to SAN on
          every tick (10-50×/sec). Each conversion clones the game state and
          runs makeMv/moveAlg for every move in the PV — with 8 MultiPV lines
          of 10+ moves each, that's 80+ makeMv calls per tick, completely
          wasted when the PV content is identical to last tick. New helper
          _clearMultiPVDisplayCache() invalidates the cache at search start.
      (2) BUG FIX: setConfigMultiPV() — when MultiPV is toggled OFF (set to 1)
          mid-search, the stale secondary PV lines (index 2..N) from the
          previous MultiPV search would persist in _multiPVLines and continue
          to be displayed until the NEXT onBestMove (seconds away). Now
          _multiPVLines and the display cache are cleared immediately when
          MultiPV is disabled, and the display refreshes instantly.
      (3) PERF: onMultiPVProgress() + onEngineProgress() — only sort
          _multiPVLines when a new line was appended (found=false). When an
          existing line was updated in-place, the array order is already
          correct (indices don't change). The sort was previously
          unconditional on every progress tick (10-50×/sec).
      (4) Also wired _clearMultiPVDisplayCache() into all three MultiPV-reset
          paths: onBestMove, restartCurrentEngine, and the engine-recovery
          path (so a recovered engine doesn't inherit stale display-cache
          signatures from the pre-crash engine).
    - ui.js (GPL v3): TWO improvements to the dirty-flag render pipeline:
      (1) PERF: _updateEvalDisplayIncremental() — added a signature check
          (_evalDispPrevSig) so we skip the innerHTML rebuild when the eval
          display content is identical to the last render. Previously, every
          DIRTY_EVAL tick (10-50×/sec during search) rebuilt the innerHTML
          even if the eval values hadn't changed (common during deep search
          where depth increments but score stays stable). The signature
          captures: setupMode, isAIThinking, emoji, desc, score, depth,
          seldepth. Invalidated on full render (renderInternal's cache-bust
          path).
      (2) No changes to _performDirtyRender's flag-routing logic — the
          "DIRTY_TOOLBAR/PANEL/MOVES → full render" branches are technically
          dead code (those flags are always accompanied by others that
          trigger the bitcount>2 full-render path), but removing them would
          make the intent less clear and risk a future regression if someone
          sets them in isolation. Left as-is.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to game-logic.js, chess960.js, pgn-standard.js, tablebase.js,
      eco-data.js, worker-pool.js, index.html.tpl.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev57 changes (CRITICAL blank-screen fix):
    - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): CRITICAL FIX — the Rev55 comment added to
      fenToState() inside the _WORKER_SOURCE template literal used backticks
      around 'parts.length<4' (i.e. `parts.length<4`). Since _WORKER_SOURCE
      is a JS template literal (delimited by backticks), the backtick inside
      the comment PREMATURELY TERMINATED the template literal, causing a
      SyntaxError that crashed the entire chess.html bundle at parse time.
      Symptom: app launches to a blank screen showing only the background
      color (#1a0a0a) — no UI, no engine init, no error visible to the user.
      Root cause: the template literal started at `const _WORKER_SOURCE = \``
      and the first backtick in the comment closed it, then the remaining
      content was parsed as top-level JS code (all invalid), producing a
      cascade of syntax errors that prevented the <script> from executing
      at all.
      Fix: removed the backticks from the comment (changed
      "from `parts.length<4` to `parts.length<2`" to
      "from parts.length<4 to parts.length<2"). The actual code change from
      Rev55 (parts.length<4 → parts.length<2) is correct and unchanged.
      Verification: node --check on the bundled chess.html JS now passes
      with exit code 0 (was failing before the fix).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev58 changes (arrow offset redesign):
    - ui.js (GPL v3): REDESIGNED the review-board arrow offset logic per user
      spec. Three guarantees now enforced:
      (1) Each color's start offset = end offset (same bias direction).
          Arrow direction is preserved; only absolute position shifts
          diagonally by color.
      (2) Reverse-overlap (A→B and B→A) only happens for SAME-color arrows.
          With same-color same-bias offset, two same-color reverse arrows
          land on the exact same line (opposite direction). Different-color
          reverse arrows land on parallel but distinct lines (different
          diagonal bias) — never collinear.
      (3) Different-color arrows NEVER overlap on the same line. Guaranteed
          by four distinct diagonal biases (B→UL, Y→LL, R→UR, G→LR).
      CHANGES from Rev54/56:
      - REMOVED the same-color multi-arrow perpendicular "fan" offset (Rev49
        feature). That offset applied DIFFERENT amounts to start (30%) vs
        end (100%), which meant same-color reverse arrows did NOT perfectly
        overlap — violating requirement (2). Now all same-color arrows
        sharing the same source+target pair overlap EXACTLY.
      - The per-color diagonal offset is the ONLY offset, applied equally
        to start and end. Offset magnitude increased from 12% to 14% of
        cell size for better visual distinction.
      - Added arrow deduplication by (color, from, to) — multiple same-color
        arrows on the same source→target pair render as ONE line.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev70 changes (2026.6.27 net-control algorithm consistency fix):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): ONE change (BUG FIX):
      (1) NET-CONTROL ALGORITHM CONSISTENCY — blue/red square candidates in
          _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations() and _computeInitialPositionAnnotations()
          changed from one-sided dominance to netCtrl-based, consistent with the
          heatmap control-info panel. Per user spec "对净控制的算法应该与'格子
          控制信息'栏中的净控制保持一致".
          Previously:
            Blue: pAtk>0 && aAtk===0 (one-sided — player has attackers, AI zero)
            Red:  aAtk>0 && pAtk===0 (one-sided — AI has attackers, player zero)
          Now:
            Blue: netCtrl>0 (player attackers > AI attackers)
            Red:  netCtrl<0 (AI attackers > player attackers)
            where netCtrl = pAtk - aAtk (same as info panel's myCtrl - opCtrl).
          Score ranks by |netCtrl| (was by one-sided attacker count). Impact: a
          square with 3 white + 1 black (netCtrl=+2) now correctly marks blue;
          previously it was NOT marked (AI had an attacker, failing one-sided).
          Spec comment items 3-4 updated.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev69 changes (2026.6.27 multi-color per square + heatmap text deletion):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): TWO changes:
      (1) MULTI-COLOR PER SQUARE — _rvCslMap changed from {square: {color}}
          (single-color overwrite) to {square: [colors]} (array preserving all
          colors). Per user spec "应该允许已被选入标记为黄色的格子再被标记为
          其它颜色" + "同一个格子上应该可以同时绘制黄色圆角矩形和其它颜色
          的方框". Render code iterates the color array: B/R/G accumulate into
          comma-separated box-shadow inset; Y sets _isYellowSquare=true. A
          square can now show both blue box-shadow AND yellow rounded-rect.
          Root cause: _rvCslMap[_h.square]={color} overwrote earlier entries.
      (2) HEATMAP TEXT DELETION — no code change in ui.js itself (the heatmap
          conditional-display text was in manuals + stats.html). See below.
    - stats.html (GPL v3): deleted the code comment quoting the heatmap
      conditional-display spec ("不含热力图控制统计数据的 PGN → 不显示热力图
      控制统计区块"). The actual conditional-display logic (_posCount===0 check)
      is unchanged — only the comment quoting the user spec was removed.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev68 changes (2026.6.27 yellow rounded-rect position fix):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): ONE change (CRITICAL BUG FIX):
      (1) YELLOW ROUNDED-RECT OVERLAY POSITION FIX — the yellow [%csl] overlay
          div was being emitted AFTER the cell div's </div> instead of INSIDE
          it. This caused position:absolute to anchor to .bgrid (the next
          positioned ancestor, via transform:translateZ(0)) instead of the cell
          div (which has position:relative). Result: all yellow overlays stacked
          near the board origin instead of on their respective cells. Fixed by
          moving the overlay emission to BEFORE the cell's </div> so it becomes
          a child of the cell div and anchors correctly. The old comment block
          describing the (broken) "emit after bgrid" approach was replaced with
          a concise current-behavior comment.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev67 changes (2026.6.27 landscape translation direction fix):
    - No changes to chess.src/ files. All Rev67 changes were in
      StabilizationHelper.java (Java layer). See
      src/main/java/com/Regalia/README.license for the Rev67 entry.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev66 changes (2026.6.27 yellow overlap + comment cleanup):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): TWO changes:
      (1) YELLOW OVERLAP ALLOWED — removed Rev65's blue/red exclusion from
          yellow-square selection. Per user spec "应该允许被标记为黄色的格子
          同时被标记为其它颜色", yellow now simply takes the top 3 by total
          attacker count, regardless of whether they're also blue or red. Both
          _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations() and
          _computeInitialPositionAnnotations() updated. Spec comment item 5
          updated.
      (2) COMMENT CLEANUP — deleted ~80 lines of stale comments: arrow-rendering
          Rev49/54/58 multi-revision narrative, Rev65/66 yellow-square redundant
          explanations, Rev62 resign-sound fix comment, Rev63 arrow-design
          change markers. Current-behavior descriptions retained.
    - index.html.tpl (AGPL v3, original): COMMENT CLEANUP — CSS
      .bwrap.stabilized comment simplified (removed Rev53/Rev64 markers and
      --stab-rot removal note).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules (game-logic.js, chess960.js, pgn-standard.js,
      worker-pool.js, ai-bridge.js, tablebase.js, eco-data.js had only comment
      cleanup — see chess.src/README.license Rev66 entries for those files
      where applicable; chess960.js/pgn-standard.js/worker-pool.js/ai-bridge.js
      comment cleanups are documented here for completeness).

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev65 changes (2026.6.27 yellow-square logic fix):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): ONE change (bug fix):
      (1) YELLOW-SQUARE LOGIC FIX in _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations() and
          _computeInitialPositionAnnotations(). Per user spec: "黄色格子应该为
          双方总控制数量(攻击该格子的棋子总数，无论棋子颜色)最多的那几个格子".
          Rev61's condition (pAtk>0 && aAtk>0 — both sides must have attackers)
          was too strict — it excluded high-total one-sided squares (e.g., 5
          white attackers + 0 black = total 5 was excluded). Rev65 changes it
          to (total>=2 — all squares with 2+ total attackers are candidates),
          then excludes squares already chosen as blue/red (one-sided dominance),
          and picks the top 3 by total. Both functions updated with the same
          logic:
            a. Collect all squares with total>=2 as yellow candidates.
            b. Select blue/red squares first (top 3 each — one-sided net control).
            c. Build a Set of blue/red square coordinates.
            d. Iterate yellow candidates (sorted by total desc), skip any in the
               blue/red set, pick top 3.
          Design rationale: one-sided-dominated squares are already labeled
          blue/red by their dominance type; yellow is reserved for the hottest
          total-control squares that aren't purely one-sided. If fewer than 3
          non-blue/red candidates exist, fewer yellow squares are emitted.
          Spec comment item 5 (around line 3503) updated to reflect the
          corrected logic.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev64 changes (2026.6.27 remove rotation + undo cache sync):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): ONE change (bug fix):
      (1) UNDO REVERTS CACHED PGN CONTENT — undoMove() now calls new
          _invalidateCachesForUndoneMoves(currentMoveCount) after restoring
          moveRecords. Previously, undoMove() restored moveRecords but did NOT
          clear cache entries for the undone moves, causing stale eval/annotation
          data to leak into re-played moves, review mode, and PGN export's
          [%eval]/[%csl]/[%cal] annotations.
          Three caches cleared:
            a. _reviewEvalCache (keyed by reviewStep, 1-based) — deletes key >
               currentMoveCount. This is the core of "background real-time
               cached PGN" — per-move eval cache backing review-mode eval bar
               and [%eval] annotations.
            b. _visualAnnotationsCache (keyed by moveIdx, 0-based) — deletes
               key >= currentMoveCount ('_initial' sentinel kept — initial-
               position annotations are independent of undo). Backs [%csl]/
               [%cal] annotations.
            c. _cachedOriginalPGN — set to null, ensuring subsequent PGN
               operations (stats page, 📚 save) use _buildPGNString() (reads
               current shorter moveRecords) instead of stale imported text.
          _redoStack is NOT cleared (undo must remain reversible). When user
          redoes, cache entries are re-created as needed.
          New function _invalidateCachesForUndoneMoves(currentMoveCount) added
          near _resetGameUIState().
    - index.html.tpl (AGPL v3, original): ONE change:
      (1) CSS .bwrap.stabilized transform changed from
          translate3d(...) rotate(var(--stab-rot,0deg)) to
          translate3d(var(--stab-x,0px),var(--stab-y,0px),0) only.
          --stab-rot CSS custom property no longer used (Rev64 removed rotation
          from anti-shake per user spec). Comment updated.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev63 changes (2026.6.27 anti-shake + arrow optimization):
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): THREE changes per user spec:
      (1) ARROW OFFSET OPTIMIZATION — offset magnitude changed from
          Math.min(3, cellSize*0.08) (3px cap + 8%) to cellSize*0.12 (12%
          no cap). Scales proportionally with cell size so the visual offset
          fraction is constant across screens. Verified safe for cellSize
          20-60px: max radial offset = cellSize/2 - 2.75 (with new strokeWidth
          1.5 and markerWidth 4); we use 12% which is well within bound.
          Cell-center formula (col*cellSize + cellSize/2) confirmed exact for
          all cell sizes — no change needed.
      (2) ARROW SHAPE REDESIGN — minimal arrow per user spec. Removed
          redundant elements: origin dot (Rev60), round linecap (Rev61→butt),
          thick stroke (2→1.5px). New arrowhead: compact 4×3 triangle (was
          5×4), refX=3.5, refY=1.5, polygon "0 0, 4 1.5, 0 3". 4×3 is the
          smallest size that still reads as a clear triangle at 30-60px cell
          sizes. Line shorten 9→4px (matches new arrowhead). stroke-opacity
          0.95→0.9 (pieces underneath remain readable). Final: thin colored
          line + small triangular point — minimal representation that
          communicates origin, target, direction, type.
      (3) No changes to the four diagonal bias directions (B→UL, Y→LL,
          R→UR, G→LR) — these guarantee different-color arrows never overlap
          on the same line.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to other JS modules.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev62 changes (2026.6.27 second-pass audit):
    - chess960.js (AGPL v3, original): CRITICAL FIX —
      _CH960_LIGHT_BISHOP_FILES and _CH960_DARK_BISHOP_FILES arrays were
      swapped. On a standard board, a1/c1/e1/g1 are DARK squares and
      b1/d1/f1/h1 are LIGHT, but the original code labeled them reversed.
      This broke 720/960 SP-IDs; SP-ID 518 produced "RNQBBKNR" instead of
      "RNBQKBNR". After fix, all 960 SP-IDs pass round-trip test. The parity
      checks in backRankToSPID() (f%2===0 vs f%2===1) were fixed in sync.
      Also corrected randomSPID() comment: P(>8 retries) is (256/65536)^8 ≈
      1.3e-19, not 0.4% as previously stated. Code was always correct.
    - game-logic.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): PERF — _ecoRecCache LRU
      no-refresh-on-hit. Cache hit returned without delete+re-insert, so hot
      entries could be evicted before cold ones. Fixed to refresh LRU on hit
      (matching _tbCache pattern). NOTE: the Chess960 castling detection
      limitation (Math.abs(to.col-from.col)===2 only works when king starts
      on col 4) was documented but NOT fixed in this round — HIGH risk,
      requires coordinated changes in 4 locations + Zobrist hash. Standard
      chess (SP-ID 518) is unaffected.
    - tablebase.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): TWO fixes —
      (1) BUG: probeTablebase() 404 misidentified as server-down. 404 means
      "position not in tablebase", not "server down". 3 × 404 falsely set
      _tbOffline=true for 60s. Now only 5xx + network errors count toward
      _tbFailCount.
      (2) BUG: PGN move-number regex (?=[a-hKQRBN]) missing 'O'. "1 O-O"
      wasn't normalized to "1. O-O" and "1" was mis-tokenized. Fixed to
      [a-hKQRBNO].
    - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3, original): TWO fixes —
      (1) BUG: PGN move-number regex same fix as tablebase.js (added 'O').
      (2) BUG: worker onerror handler called .delete() on _workerPending Map
      during for...of iteration. Fixed to snapshot keys via Array.from()
      before deletion.
    - pgn-standard.js (AGPL v3, original): REDUNDANCY — removed dead
      `let lineLen=0` in composePGN() (wrapping logic uses curLine.length,
      never reads lineLen).
    - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): FOUR fixes —
      (1) BUG: c.mate||0 lost the mate:0 vs mate:null distinction. Fixed to
      c.mate!=null?c.mate:0.
      (2) REDUNDANCY: removed dead _importedStartColor ternary (variable
      never declared, typeof guard always true, entire startColor computation
      was dead code).
      (3) SIMPLIFY: removed redundant depth>0 check in onEngineProgress
      (already guaranteed by line 1854 if(depth<=0)return).
      (4) PERF: _updateMultiPVDisplay() early-exit when !isHintLoading —
      previously computed hintParts/signatures/cache checks 10-50×/sec
      during AI thinking but discarded the result.
    - ui.js (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): THREE fixes —
      (1) BUG: _resignGame() called undefined _playSound('lose'). The typeof
      guard prevented ReferenceError, so the resign sound was silently never
      played. Now calls playSound('gameover').
      (2) PERF: eval chart label loop used _reviewEvalCache.get() (refreshes
      LRU) instead of peek() in a read-only iteration. Fixed to peek().
      (3) SIMPLIFY: two instances of _prevMvEval?_prevMvEval.eval:0 ternary
      simplified to _prevMvEval.eval (outer if already guarantees non-null).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - No changes to eco-data.js, index.html.tpl.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev61 changes (2026.6.27 development plan):
    - ui.js (GPL v3): THREE changes:
      (1) YELLOW SQUARE LOGIC FIX in _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations() and
          _computeInitialPositionAnnotations(): yellow-square selection
          changed from `total>=2` to `pAtk>0 && aAtk>0` (both sides must
          have attackers). Previously, single-side-dominated squares (e.g.
          5 white attackers + 0 black = total 5) were misclassified as
          yellow — they should be BLUE (player net control). Per user spec
          "黄色格=双方总控制高格(当前未正确实现)". Now correctly distinguishes
          one-sided dominance (blue/red) from contested heat (yellow).
      (2) ARROW STROKE-LINECAP changed from "round" to "butt" in the
          review-board SVG arrow lines. The round linecap created a small
          semi-circle at the arrow's start (no marker there), visually
          reading as an "extra dot" — contradicting user spec "箭头末端没有
          多余的圆点". Butt linecap eliminates the visible dot.
      (3) No other changes to the arrow offset logic (same four diagonal
          biases: B→UL, Y→LL, R→UR, G→LR; same cap of 3px / 8% of cell size).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev60 changes (arrow cleanup + rotation limit):
    - ui.js (GPL v3): THREE changes per user spec:
      (1) REMOVED the origin dot (circle element) from the review-board SVG
          arrows. Previously each arrow had a small filled circle (r=2.5) at
          its origin to mark the source. User requested removal — the
          arrowhead at the end is sufficient to indicate direction.
      (2) CALIBRATED the per-color diagonal offset magnitude to stay within
          cell bounds. Reduced from Math.min(6, cellSize*0.14) to
          Math.min(3, cellSize*0.08). The previous 14% (capped at 6px) could
          cause arrow endpoints to exceed the cell boundary on small screens.
          The new 8% (capped at 3px) is well within the safe zone for all
          cell sizes ≥ 30px.
      (3) No other changes to the arrow offset logic (same four diagonal
          biases: B→UL, Y→LL, R→UR, G→LR).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.


  v1.0.6 (2026.6.27) changes:
    - game-logic.js (GPL v3): NEW _castleSide(mv) helper — unambiguous
      castling detection using explicit mv.castle flag (set by pseudoMoves)
      with a destination-column+distance fallback for moves reconstructed
      from PGN/UCI. Replaces the legacy Math.abs(to.col-from.col)===2
      pattern which only works for standard chess (Chess960 king may move
      1 col to castle). NEW _lastAnimMv global for animateMove castling
      detection. pseudoMoves() now tags castling moves with castle:'kingside'/
      'queenside'. makeMv()/makeMvInPlace() CRITICAL FIX: save the rook
      BEFORE moving the king (Chess960 rook source may === king destination),
      suppress capture for castling, place saved rook at destination after
      king moves. moveAlg() uses _castleSide(). animateMove() uses
      _lastAnimMv+_castleSide for Chess960 rook position. Zobrist hash
      update uses actual rook from/to cols (was hardcoded 0/3/5/7).
      _finishAnim() clears _lastAnimMv. loading_title updated to v1.0.6.
      NEW i18n strings: gray_disabled_by_eco_book, gray_disabled_by_chess960.
    - chess960.js (AGPL v3): No changes (castling helpers unchanged).
    - pgn-standard.js (AGPL v3): No changes.
    - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): Comment fix — removed backtick from a
      comment inside the _WORKER_SOURCE template literal (Rev57-class bug
      that prematurely terminated the template string, causing blank screen).
    - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): NEW _sanitizeFenForEngine(fen) — strips
      inconsistent castling rights (e.g. 'q' with no black rook on a8)
      before sending to Stockfish, preventing engine hangs. Applied to all
      engineEval/engineEvalDeep/engineHint/engineGo/engineGoTimed/startPonder
      calls. _aiOpponentNameWithLevel() now appends the actual Skill Level
      value (e.g. "SL20") for SL mode. _uciToSimple() castling detection
      simplified to distance-based (2+ cols). Engine Config dialog Skill
      Level gray-out unified (only buttons dimmed, not surrounding text).
      ENGINE_VERSION updated to v1.0.6.
    - tablebase.js (GPL v3): importPGN() FIX — now sets _setupFEN from
      result.startFEN so PGN round-trip preserves [SetUp]/[FEN] headers.
      applySANMove() Chess960 castling fix — finds king's actual column
      instead of hardcoding col 4.
    - eco-data.js (AGPL v3): No changes.
    - ui.js (GPL v3): NEW _getCastlingRookSquares()/_getCastlingRookForClick()
      for king-then-rook castling gesture. NEW _computeCastlingRookSetForSelection()
      pure helper. _updateChangedSquares() FIX — now adds/removes castle-ring
      marker in the lightweight update path (was only in renderInternal,
      causing marker to not appear on selection and get stuck after appearing).
      sqClick() castling gesture handler. executeMove() FIX — copies castle
      flag from legalMvs to mv object. _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations()
      FIX — restores castle flag from moveRecords.isCastling. ECO panels
      hidden in Chess960 mode. _startGameImpl() disables _ecoEnabled in
      Chess960. New Game dialog gray-out unified (only toggle dimmed).
      Portrait dialog CSS. Scroll preservation for .dlg/.panel/.review-moves/
      .op-list. Analyze-all off-by-one fix (_totalSteps=moveRecords.length,
      reviewAnalyzeAll iterates 1..N, _reviewAnalyzeAdvance terminates at
      nextStep>N). Version strings updated to v1.0.6 (3 locations).
    - index.html.tpl (AGPL v3): NEW .castle-ring CSS (golden dashed pulse
      animation). Portrait New Game dialog CSS (max-width:460px, tighter
      padding, stacked inputs, ECO search wrap). Title updated to v1.0.6.
    - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.
    - stats.html (GPL v3): executeMove() FIX — same castling rook-save fix
      as game-logic.js makeMv(). Scroll position preservation (window.scrollY
      saved/restored across #content innerHTML replacement).

v1.0.8 (2026.6.30) changes:
  The v1.0.8 release completely redesigns the move animation and sound effect
  system (Phase 22) and adds light mode support. See the HTML user manuals at
  Manual/Regalia-v1.0.8-manual-{zh,en}.html, Appendix A "版本更新日志" /
  "Version Changelog" for the full per-phase changelog.

  Phase 22 (v1.0.8) summary:
    - game-logic.js: COMPLETE removal of old animation system
      (_lastAnimPieceType, _lastAnimTarget, _lastCaptureFlag, _lastCheckFlag,
      _landingAnimActive, _landingAnimTimer, _animFinishTimer,
      _startLandingTimer(), old animateMove() body 170+ lines). New
      personified piece animations via Web Animations API: _animPawn,
      _animKnight, _animBishop, _animRook, _animQueen, _animKing, each
      with unique cubic-bezier easing + translate3d + scale + rotate +
      drop-shadow keyframes. New _triggerBoardShake() for rook/king
      landing shake. New _playPieceSound() / _playCastleSound() for
      audioEngine integration. _animGen generation counter retained.
      _reattachActiveAnimations() retained. animateMove() signature
      preserved. prefers-reduced-motion respected. Chess960 _kingStayedPut
      respected.
    - ui.js: COMPLETE removal of old sound system (audioCtx, getAudioCtx(),
      old playSound(type) body). New ChessAudioEngine class (pure Web Audio
      API synthesis, no audio files). New audioEngine global variable. New
      playSound(type) maps to engine. 13 cross-file references to old
      animation state adapted. soundOn + toggleSound() + toolbar button
      preserved. New _isLightMode() + _hdrKingIconHTML() for header king
      icon light/dark switch.
    - ai-bridge.js: New _isLightMode() + _loadingKingIconHTML() for loading
      overlay king icon light/dark switch. _showLoadingOverlay() uses CSS
      variables (var(--overlay-bg), var(--accent2), var(--muted),
      var(--input-bg), var(--accent)) for theme-aware styling.
    - index.html.tpl: :root now declares color-scheme:dark light + light
      theme variables via @media(prefers-reduced-scheme:light). Old CSS
      animations removed (pawnStep, knightJump, bishopGlide, rookSlide,
      queenGlide, kingStep, captureFlash, captureCore, .sq .pc.anim-*,
      .move-anim.anim-* transitions). New shakeLight/shakeHeavy keyframes
      added. prefers-reduced-motion updated. 13 hardcoded component colors
      replaced with CSS variables.
    - stats.html: :root now declares color-scheme:dark light + light theme
      variables via @media(prefers-color-scheme:light).
    - chess.html: rebuilt from the above 4 source files.

    - 7th/8th supplements (2026-06-30):
      * game-l: validateSetupPosition() now calls syncHash(s) after
        modifying castlingRights/enPassTarget (castling rights loss fix).
        _finishAnim() removed all manual opacity restoration (was causing
        "_srcRookPc is not defined" error and "piece returns to source"
        visual artifact). .sq .pc removed stale transition:transform .1s
        and will-change:transform,opacity (old CSS landing animation
      * index.html.tpl: last-move highlight rolled back from outline to
        box-shadow; uses CSS variables for both dark/light modes.
      * ui.js: global click listener's closest() selector added .hdr-btn,
        .hdr-btn-lg (ℹ️ button sound fix).
      * StockNative.java: added isSystemMode() method (already done in 5th
        supplement, noted here for completeness).
      * StatsActivity.java: added isSystemDarkMode() method.

    - Light mode system-switch bug fix (v1.0.8 Phase 22 fifth supplement):
      * ai-bridge.js: _isLightMode() now prioritizes AndroidBridge.isSystemDarkMode()
        over window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: light)'). New
        _applySystemTheme() function sets document.documentElement data-theme
        attribute at startup.
      * index.html.tpl: Added html[data-theme="light"] and html[data-theme="dark"]
        attribute selectors alongside @media(prefers-color-scheme:light) — same
        silver palette, dual-channel triggering for Xiaomi HyperOS 3 compatibility.
      * stats.html: Added html[data-theme] selectors + init() applies data-theme.
      * StockfishNative.java: New @JavascriptInterface isSystemDarkMode() method
        reads UiModeManager.getNightMode() (Android 5.0+ compatible).

    - Light mode silver palette redesign (v1.0.8 Phase 22 third supplement):
      * index.html.tpl: light mode @media(prefers-color-scheme:light) palette
        redesigned to silver tones (#f0f0f3/#e0e0e5/#2c2c34/#6a6a76/#4a4a52).
        40+ hardcoded component colors replaced with CSS variables. 15 new
        theme variables added. 4 utility classes added (.hdr-btn, .hdr-btn-lg,
        .chip-active, .chip-inactive).
      * ui.js: inline-style hardcoded colors replaced with CSS variables
        (header buttons, PGN cache chips, recovery UI, ECO card, tablebase
        card, review chart, toggle dot, range slider). _hdrKingIconHTML keeps
        gold gradient border (design intent).
      * ai-bridge.js: showToast() background/border/shadow replaced with CSS
        variables. Engine config dialog #221015→var(--card).
      * stats.html: light mode synced to silver palette.

    - Sound & animation optimization (v1.0.8 Phase 22 second supplement):
      * game-logic.js: _playPieceSound / _playCastleSound now check soundOn
        before playing (bug fix: previously bypassed the soundOn guard, so
        move/castle sounds played even when muted). ANIM_DURATIONS.queen
        420→500ms; ANIM_EASINGS.queen changed to cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1)
        (same as king); _animQueen: keyframes 20→16, scale 0.05→0.08, landing
        phase adds compression, onfinish triggers _triggerBoardShake('heavy')
        (same as king). _animKnight: keyframes 24→18. _animKing: keyframes
        28→24. loading_title i18n string "Regalia v1.0.7"→"Regalia v1.0.8".
      * ui.js: toggleSound() now calls audioEngine.setEnabled(soundOn) to sync
        the engine's enabled flag.
      * ChessWebViewClient.java: version comment "Version: v1.0.7"→"v1.0.8".

    - Scene sound expansion (v1.0.8 Phase 22 supplement): 14 new personified
      scene sounds added to ChessAudioEngine in ui.js (playDeselect, playUndo,
      playRedo, playFlip, playNewGame, playEnterReview, playExitReview,
      playSetupToggle, playResign, playCopy, playError, playAiThinkStart,
      playAiThinkEnd). playSound(type) type parameter expanded from 7 to 21.
      Smart toast sound (_playToastSound) auto-detects success/error from
      message keywords. Sound trigger points added to sqClick, undoMove,
      redoMove, flipBoard, _startGameImpl, enterReview, exitReview,
      toggleSetup, _resignGame, getHint, doAIMove, onBestMove, toggleSound,
      toggleLang. ai-bridge.js: PIECE_SELECT now also triggers playSound('select');
      onBestMove triggers playSound('aiThinkEnd'). game-logic.js: doAIMove
      triggers playSound('aiThinkStart'); toggleLang triggers playSound('select').

    - Post-release emergency bug fixes (same day):
      * ai-bridge.js: removed residual _landingAnimActive=false and
        _landingAnimTimer cleanup in engine-error handler (variables removed
        in v1.0.8 redesign).
      * game-logic.js: _requestStockfishMove's if(!_landingAnimActive)render()
        changed to if(!animationInProgress)render(). _finishAnim(): moved
        el.remove()/rookEl.remove() before _myGen check to prevent DOM leakage
        from stale closures.
      * ui.js: _updateSingleSq sig variable's trailing +animCls removed
        (animCls was deleted, residual reference caused ReferenceError).
        _hdrKingIconHTML(): fixed "♚\uFE0E;" → "\u265A\uFE0E" (extra
        semicolon was displayed as literal). executeMove(): removed duplicate
        playSound('move'/'capture'/'castle') calls (animateMove's internal
        _playPieceSound/_playCastleSound handles these; executeMove now only
        handles promote/check special cases). ANIMATION_DEFER_MS increased
        from 300ms to 560ms to match new animation durations (King=520ms).
      * index.html.tpl: removed 4 redundant CSS variables (--hdr-king-color,
        --hdr-king-stroke, --hdr-king-shadow, --hdr-king-sym) that were never
        referenced (king icon switching is JS-driven).
      * ai-bridge.js: _loadingKingIconHTML() unified to use Unicode escapes
        (\u2654/\u265A) instead of literal ♔/♚ characters.

  License classification: game-logic.js, ai-bridge.js, ui.js remain GPL v3
  (DroidFish-derived); chess960.js, eco-data.js, index.html.tpl remain AGPL v3
  (original); stats.html remains GPL v3 (DroidFish-derived PGN parsing). The
  new ChessAudioEngine class is original code embedded in ui.js (GPL v3 per
  DroidFish derivation). No new third-party code was introduced in v1.0.8.

v1.0.7 (2026.6.28-29) changes:
  The v1.0.7 release spans 17 phases. Rather than duplicate the per-phase
  detail here (which is already exhaustively documented in the HTML user
  manuals at Manual/Regalia-v1.0.7-manual-{zh,en}.html, Appendix A
  "版本更新日志" / "Version Changelog"), this file lists only the
  license-relevant structural changes. See the HTML manuals for the full
  per-phase changelog with user-facing descriptions.

  Phase summary (newest first):
    - Phase 17: Chess960 castling "king self-capture" critical bug fix +
      review "Analyze All" button auto-refresh + adoption of 5 reasonable
      Kimi-audit suggestions. Bug fixes:
        * game-logic.js makeMv / makeMvInPlace: skip king move entirely
          when castling AND from===to (king already on castling destination
          square per Fischer Random Chess rule "castling in place").
        * game-logic.js unmakeMv: detect castlingRook && from===to and skip
          the king-position restore (rook is independently restored via
          castlingRook field).
        * game-logic.js animateMove: when castling AND from===to, skip the
          king overlay (no dx=0,dy=0 "no-op" animation); also added
          prefers-reduced-motion JS-side check that skips the entire
          animation path when the user has reduced-motion enabled.
        * ui.js: new _rvAnalyzeBtnLabel() pure function and
          _updateReviewAnalyzeBtn() that refreshes the analyze-all button
          via textContent (no DOM rebuild); button gets
          id="review-analyze-btn".
        * ai-bridge.js onEngineEval: now calls _updateReviewAnalyzeBtn()
          after each eval so the button switches to "All Analyzed" the
          moment the last step's eval completes (whether batch or manual).
        * stats.html: _escFEN adds backtick escaping; new _cloneStatsState
          replaces JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(state)) in selectVariationMove
          (~10x faster, type-safe); board max-width 360px → 400px.
        * index.html.tpl: .bgrid gets content-visibility:auto (off-screen
          render skip; contain:strict NOT added to preserve responsive
          CELL recalculation).
      Files: game-logic.js, ai-bridge.js, ui.js, index.html.tpl, chess.html,
      stats.html.
    - Phase 18: _reviewEvalCache LRU eviction + review move-list virtual list
      + 11 first-principles code-review fixes.
      Performance breakthroughs:
        * ai-bridge.js: _reviewEvalCache now has MAX_ENTRIES=2000 soft cap
          with _evictIfOverCap() on set(); Map.keys() iteration order = LRU
          order; skips _reviewEvalRequestedStep; persistence preserves LRU
          order via Array.from(m.entries()); backward-compatible.
        * ui.js: review move-list virtual list (RV_VIRTUAL_THRESHOLD=80,
          RV_OVERSCAN=10). Shared _buildReviewMovesInnerHTML() eliminates
          ~40 lines of landscape/portrait duplication; passive scroll
          listener; 80ms-debounced _refreshReviewMovesOnly() replaces only
          .review-moves innerHTML; first-render measures avgRowH via rAF;
          _resetRvVirtualState() on enter/exit review, new game, import.
      Bug fixes:
        * game-logic.js unmakeMv: Chess960 board corruption when rook
          destination = king source (~half of SP-ID positions). Fixed:
          save rook piece in undo.castlingRook.piece; restore from saved
          piece; only null cr.to if it doesn't coincide with king source.
        * game-logic.js makeMvInPlace: castling-rights not cleared for rook
          move/capture (findCastlingRooks called after mutation). Fixed:
          snapshot delta before mutation (_movingRookSide/_capturedRookSide).
        * game-logic.js animateMove: stale-_finishAnim race. Fixed:
          _animFinishTimer + _animGen generation counter.
        * ai-bridge.js: single-step review eval missing safety timer. Fixed:
          45s timer. Also removed dead if(isCheck) block in reduced-motion
          path.
        * ui.js: virtual-list window forced back to active step on every
          render → flicker. Fixed: track _lastRenderReviewStep. Also clear
          _rvScrollRefreshTimer in renderInternal; _resetRvVirtualState in
          import wrappers.
        * pgn-standard.js: comment-flattening polluted movetext (latent).
          Fixed: remove entire comment (braces + body) matching tablebase.js.
        * worker-pool.js: missing unclosed-brace handling (latent). Fixed.
      Files: ai-bridge.js, game-logic.js, ui.js, pgn-standard.js,
      worker-pool.js, chess.html.
    - Phase 19: comprehensive first-principles code review (7 subagents,
      28k lines, 20+ critical fixes).
      Critical bug fixes:
        * ai-bridge.js: _reviewEvalCache corruption race (cache-hit/terminal
          fast paths didn't clear debounce timer → stale callback overwrote
          cache). Fixed: clear _reviewEvalDebounceTimer + increment
          _evalStaleGen on both fast paths.
        * ai-bridge.js: cross-mode stale callback race (review callback
          passed normal-mode gen check after exitReview). Fixed: capture
          _evalRequestReviewMode at request time; reject cross-mode.
        * game-logic.js: animateMove reduced-motion path race (Phase 18
          _animGen fix didn't cover reduced-motion early return). Fixed:
          cancel timer + bump gen + set 3 missing flags.
        * ui.js: reviewAnalyzeAll completion didn't restore eval vars from
          cache → eval bar showed wrong step; reviewCritical not recomputed
          → 💥/❌ markers missing. Fixed: call reviewGoTo(returnStep) +
          _findCriticalMoves().
        * tablebase.js: PGN [%eval] placeholder offset (FEN-start PGNs where
          Black is to move had evals attach to wrong step). Fixed: apply
          _placeholderOffset when populating eval/annotation/comment caches.
        * ui.js: setupRedoStack not cleared on Reset/Clear Board. Fixed.
        * ui.js: _resignGame clock leak (gameClocks.running=false no-op).
          Fixed: clearInterval(gameClockTimerId).
        * ui.js: _pendingStatsImportPGN global race. Fixed: close over
          pgnText directly.
        * stats.html: Backspace re-opened dismissed import-back dialog.
          Fixed: check _statsImportBackDialogVisible flag.
        * stats.html: double safe-area-inset-top → header jump on first
          scroll. Fixed: body top padding 0; .hdr owns safe-area.
        * StockfishNative.java: engineProcess/Reader/Writer/readerThread/
          _engineExecutor all declared volatile (thread safety).
        * StockfishNative.java: stopAndWaitForBestmove timeout stale-bestmove
          corruption. Fixed: set _discardingPonderBestmove=true on timeout.
        * ChessApp.java: UncaughtExceptionHandler swallowed Error (OOM/
          StackOverflow) on worker threads. Fixed: chain Error to default
          handler.
        * EngineService.java: lastStatusInfo not volatile. Fixed.
        * tablebase.js: probeTablebase JSON parse error miscounted as
          offline. Fixed: separate try/catch for resp.json().
      Performance & functionality:
        * ai-bridge.js: notification throttle buffers pending info; PGN
          export eval tag uses peek() not get() (LRU churn); WDL negative
          percentage fix; onEngineError restart timer leak fix.
        * stats.html: CSP added (defense-in-depth for XSS).
      Redundancy cleanup:
        * ai-bridge.js: removed stale "Unlimited cache size" comment.
        * stats.html: removed dead renderPGN()/renderMoveNotation(); removed
          duplicate body rule in portrait media query; added full Copyright
          + GPL v3 license block to <head> (was missing).
      Files: ai-bridge.js, game-logic.js, ui.js, tablebase.js, stats.html,
      StockfishNative.java, ChessApp.java, EngineService.java, chess.html.
    - Phase 20: UX refinements (4 items).
        * ui.js: review eval bar font .75rem/.7rem → .85rem/.8rem (portrait/
          landscape); emoji .95rem → 1.1rem/1.05rem; max-height 1.9em → 2.4em;
          padding 3px 8px → 5px 10px. Analyze button font .7rem → .8rem;
          min-height 28px → 34px; padding 6px 10px.
        * game-logic.js: move animation durations slowed ~30% (pawn 180→240,
          knight 240→320, bishop 210→280, rook 180→240, queen 260→340,
          king 210→280). 120fps preserved (GPU-composited).
        * index.html.tpl: CSS transition durations updated to match JS
          (.18-.26s → .24-.34s). Landscape .bsec margin-right:10px for
          anti-shake clearance. Portrait .dov asymmetric padding
          (padding-top:18vh) for "slightly above center" dialog positioning.
          .dlg:not([style*="max-width"]) selector distinguishes fullscreen
          vs small dialogs; fullscreen uses negative margin to cancel
          padding-top. Landscape .review-bottom buttons slightly enlarged.
      Files: game-logic.js, ui.js, index.html.tpl, chess.html.
    - Phase 21: bug fixes (3 items).
        * index.html.tpl: Portrait dialog positioning precision fix —
          padding-top:18vh/padding-bottom:10px → padding-top:10px/
          padding-bottom:12vh (content center 59vh → 44vh, true "slightly
          above center"). Fullscreen dialog negative margins updated to
          cancel both paddings.
        * index.html.tpl: Landscape .bsec overflow:hidden → overflow-x:
          visible; overflow-y:hidden (anti-shake translate3d no longer
          clipped by .bsec). Rolled back Phase 20's ineffective
          margin-right:10px. .panel overflow-x:auto added (wide content
          scrolls within panel, not clipped by .main).
        * game-logic.js: _antiShake isLandscape?0:6 → 8 in BOTH
          orientations (matches MAX_DISPLACEMENT_PX=8.0f in
          StabilizationHelper.java). CELL calculation now reserves 8px for
          anti-shake in landscape too.
      Files: game-logic.js, index.html.tpl, chess.html.
    - Phase 16: final comprehensive review. Bug fix: tablebase.js
      _parsePGN [%eval] off-by-one (mid-branch used _moveCount instead of
      _moveCount-1; trailing branch used _moveCount+1 instead of
      _moveCount). Redundancy cleanup: worker-pool.js removed second
      rawTokens walk (reuse rootFrame.tokens); tablebase.js removed
      redundant selective cache-clear in importPGN; pgn-standard.js
      removed unused varStack; ui.js removed dead ternary in
      _findCriticalMoves; updated 4 stale "1-based" comments in
      ai-bridge.js and ui.js; removed 3 debug console.logs and their
      unused _populated/_populatedVa/_populatedCm counters in tablebase.js.
      Files: tablebase.js, worker-pool.js, pgn-standard.js, ui.js,
      ai-bridge.js, chess.html.
    - Phase 15: review "Analyze All" now includes step 0 (the initial
      position). _totalSteps changed from moveRecords.length to
      moveRecords.length+1; reviewAnalyzeAll() and _reviewAnalyzeAdvance()
      now iterate steps 0..N inclusive. Also fixes the first move's
      delta/classification, the chart's x=0 data point, and critical-move
      detection for the first move. Files: ui.js, chess.html.
    - Phase 14: review eval-bar fonts enlarged (.75rem / .7rem), max-height
      capped to single line (max-height:1.9em; overflow:hidden;
      white-space:nowrap); review trend chart resized (min 120px, max 200px
      in both orientations). Files: ui.js, index.html.tpl, chess.html.
    - Phase 13: misreport cleanup — removed the setupMode defensive guard
      in computeVisibleEpMark() (game-logic.js); fixed toggleSetup() exit
      path to clear setupEpMark/setupCastleMarks (ui.js); simplified
      enterReview() reviewBaseState/reviewStates cloneS comments (ui.js);
      removed dead _boardWidthPx variable (ui.js); fixed enterReview()
      no-piece branch to use cloneS (ui.js). No license classification
      changes. Files: game-logic.js, ui.js, chess.html.
    - Phase 12: ⚡ marker entering-setup-mode root-cause fix (toggleSetup
      reverse-maps enPassantTarget back to pawn's square); review eval bar
      width:100% + box-sizing:border-box; trend chart min height 80px.
      Files: ui.js, index.html.tpl, chess.html.
    - Phase 11: review eval bar/chart sizing (fonts .62rem/.58rem, chart
      min 80px). (The ⚡ marker review-mode fix originally in this phase
      was confirmed as a misreport in Phase 13 and cleaned up.)
    - Phase 10: landscape board cap 60px, panel min 240px + 30% proportional,
      review eval bar/chart sizing. (The ⚡ marker defensive fix originally
      in this phase was confirmed as a misreport in Phase 13 and cleaned up;
      the enPassantTarget pawn-color verification is retained as a valid
      defense.)
    - Phase 9: (REMOVED — was a misreport. enterReview() always deriving
      reviewBaseState from stateHistory[0] and reviewStates cloneS deep
      copies are retained as correct design, not misreport fixes.)
    - Phase 8: landscape board oversize fix, dialog button fix, setup marker
      polish. (The ⚡ marker review-mode fix originally in this phase was
      confirmed as a misreport in Phase 13; the _exitSetupImpl() clear of
      setupEpMark is retained as correct transient-field cleanup.)
    - Phase 7: board sizing root-cause fix, dialog layout, setup marker
      polish.
    - Phase 6: landscape right-edge root-cause fix (body padding → #app
      margin), setup marker feature polish.
    - Phase 5: board sizing and portrait layout optimization.
    - Phase 4: Chess960 / X-FEN rule correctness overhaul (findCastlingRooks,
      findCastlingRookForSide, Shredder-FEN, UCI_Chess960 king-takes-rook).
    - Phase 3: portrait UI redesign from scratch (@media(orientation:portrait)
      no width threshold + vw/clamp()), computeVisibleCastleMarks/
      computeVisibleEpMark pure functions, always-Chess960 castling rule.
    - Phase 2: Quick Toolbar (Undo/Redo/Flip/AI-Hint/Control-Range moved
      below board), setup-mode 🔁/⚡ manual marker buttons, removed
      recomputeCastlingRights() dead function.
    - Phase 1: code-review bug fixes (critical-move cache invalidation,
      lightweight board update castling-rook marker, engine-notification
      throttle cache, stats.html PGN comment XSS, CSP Blob Worker,
      cross-game eval-cache pollution), About dialog GitHub hyperlinks,
      back-button handling, merged duplicate HTML-escape functions.

  License classification: unchanged from v1.0.6 — game-logic.js, ai-bridge.js,
  pgn-standard.js, worker-pool.js, tablebase.js, stats.html remain GPL v3
  (DroidFish-derived); chess960.js, eco-data.js, index.html.tpl remain AGPL v3
  (original). No new third-party code was introduced in v1.0.7.

