v1.0.8 Phase 31 (2026.7.1):
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3): getCtrlMap allocation reduction via hidden-class
    stability — extracted a _newCtrlCell factory so all 64 cell objects share
    the same V8 hidden class, improving inline-cache hit rates for downstream
    cm[r][c].white / .black property access in the hot rendering loop. Could
    not reuse a single buffer across calls because callers cache the result
    (cachedCtrlMap keyed by gameState.hash) and a concurrent
    _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations call (postState.board, a DIFFERENT
    board) would corrupt the cached data.
  - eco-data.js (AGPL v3): searchEco pre-indexing — _ensureEcoParsed now
    pre-computes uppercase _nameU and _familyU fields on each opening object
    at parse time. searchEco reads these directly instead of calling
    toUpperCase() on every opening's name AND family on EVERY keystroke
    (was 2 × ~3000 = 6000 toUpperCase() allocations per search; now 0).
    Also added early-exit when results reach 20 (the slice cap) to avoid
    scanning all ~3000 openings when the query is common (e.g. "king").

v1.0.8 Phase 32 (2026.7.1):
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): _escJs now also HTML-escapes < > & (was XSS
    vector via path containing "<script>"). Regex includes & in char class.
  - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): added _MAX_QUEUE_SIZE=50 cap; rejects excess
    tasks immediately so callers fall back to sync execution.
  - pgn-standard.js (AGPL v3): all parseInt() in parseTimeControl now pass
    radix 10 (lint-clean, future-proof).
  - game-logic.js (GPL v3): No changes.
  - ui.js (GPL v3): No changes.
  - index.html.tpl (combined): No changes.

